76561198034817134,Not Recommended,276810,32376951,Posted: 12 June,all,Bitches_N_Bullets,"Despite what you may read in most reviews of this game, it is not actually that difficult of a game. Complicated? yes. Difficult? no. You develop your dudes outside of battle, always seeming to have to work with far less money than you think you should have. The battles themselves are basically all about moving into just the right spots to exploit the tact-less AI. The game rewards positioning above all else, and it is not hard to learn where to place your dudes to avoid walking home missing a few arms and legs.I think that the ""difficulty"" of the game comes from the sudden and severe way in which you can be punished for abandoning safe positioning. You know that guy you've been training and building up since day 1? Well you moved him just a little too far out to pick up some wyrdstone and he got surrounded for an AI beating that ended up killing him permanently. Also, you should always elect to choose your own positioning before battles, or just avoid choosing the battles where you are forced to split your group up into 3+ groups. You will never be rewarded for splitting up your party during combat. Once you get combat (read: positioning) down, you will get pretty bored pretty quickly realizing how stale the action is, how cardboard the environments really are, and how totally annoying it is that your agile jumping/climbing guy just lost his leg."
