76561198027994280,Not Recommended,276810,31962306,Posted: 25 May,all,Ismaru,"While I'm not one to shy away from a tough game, this one was just too much for me. It's an awesome game but I wish I could just ""git gud"" because it's so hard that I rather spend time on something else, and my recommendation is that you do too.ProsIt's a game set in the awesome Warhammer world!Graphics are OK - it seemed groggy initially but there's actually a lot of eye for detailThe music, the entire atmosphere in Mordheim is well doneIt's a fun and pretty unique take on the tactics genre.ConsThe game is overly complex; thankfully there was a good tutorial but I still felt I didn't even know half of everything there is to know.It's very hard.The game is really unforgiving and the ""RNG"" is very frustrating. I get ganged myself and don't stand a chance, I gang up on a novice small unit with 3 man and it manages to stun and crit someone to death. Aaaaarghhhh!!The game is always in ironman mode (AKA no saving in between, what happens happens). You can stop whenever you want and the game will pick up where you left off, but you can never ""go back in time"". I even tried alt-f4'ing in the middle of a game (yes, I got that desperate), and upon restarting I just landed right back into the one-sided slaughter that was going on.There is no clear progression path. In fact, I even de-leveled a bit once I started losing some valuable characters that I had to replace with noobies, while the enemies didn't seem to get weaker. I seemed to slowly spiral downwards into a place where I couldn't afford paying my troops and only replaced them with weaker ones.I would like to revisit Mordheim sometime in the future, even in it's current state. But only if I'm in a sadistic mood and I feel like really getting challenged. Also I think this game could've been a far bigger success if it was a bit easier. If it at least not force ironman mode I think it would've made a big difference.Was this review useful to you?Please also check out the Izzy Reviews Curator pagefor regular updates on reviews for other games!"
