76561198000507953,Recommended,276810,34619879,Posted: 30 August,all,Chuckledunk,"Did you like X-COM? If you didn't, you probably won't like this.Mordheim is a game about playing the odds and testing your ability to recover. Yes, it's heavily RNG. So is any tabletop game that uses dice. Much like with D&D however, it's possible to maximize your odds of success through smart positioning and, as the game progresses and you can afford more skills and spells, tactical choices.This is not a fast paced game. That is important to note. There are often waits while the other team is going, and that can get boring if you don't have a show in the background or something else to do for brief spans. However, having to wait for the AI to move isn't exactly a new thing with turn based strategy games, I remember having some pretty lengthy waits in Sid Meier's Alpha Centauri.A lot of people have some pretty strong opinions about how saving works here. I was pretty annoyed at it myself while I was still learning my way around the game, but now that I have I kinda understand the difference in playstyle it leads to and while it may not be for everyone it IS rather engaging. Unlike most other games, your every decision matters. You can take nothing back. If you want to test your ability to respond to unfavorable situations, this game will give you plenty of chances to do so, and it makes victory all the sweeter when you manage to outplay a stronger enemy.If you are going to pick up this game, you should probably accept that, in all likelyness, you are going to be pretty bad at it at first. That's normal, it's got a bit of a learning curve, and anyone I know who's good at the game has had their share of bad defeats and abandoned warbands. On the bright side, part of the progression is independant of your specific warband, meaning that if you play a lot and start a new game, your new warband will start off with more resources and a higher level than they would otherwise.Personally I haven't suffered from any of the bugs that I'm seeing people talk about. I'm not doubting that they've run into them, but I've never had my characters get stuck in terrain, I've never dealt with it crashing, and at least on my machine it's been quite reliable in its performance.If you have patience and a tactical mind, this game is great fun."
