76561198026564395,Recommended,276810,15419659,"Posted: 17 April, 2015",all,cultleaderxx,"Looks to have potential. I am excited about playing this game as of Sept. 27 2015. It has a very good feel to it. Like playing one of the Games Workshop minature tabletop games. You can change a ton of bits on each model and paint it several different colors and schemes. The game is almost like the table top game as well with the item selections, the spells, skills, attributes, and perks all adjustable and customizeable.There is now progression and consequences, in my first battle my hero was surrounded and defeated, in the after action report it was revealed that the hero had been mortally wounded and lost an arm. The model was forever afterwards missing a limb and could not hold a shield anymore. There are objectives during combat and the AI isn't terrible at ganging up on you and isolating single units. (not certain at this time if the AI will complete objectives of it's own or if it has them) but the game has a sense of RPG to it now.Money well spent as the developer keeps pushing out new content and seems to be working on something that could be unique in the Games Workshop videogames; a digital version of the table top game. 4 races at this time and hoping to see undead, orks, and elves, but a very solid game at this point with most bugs stompped out regularly as they creep up. I would recommend this game to any GW fans of the old mordheim and inquisitor games.P.S. I would love to see skins and maps for Inquisitor/Necromunda using this engine, all the mechanics are similar enough to make it a fantastic 40k experience."
,Recommended,276810,24748779,"Posted: 6 August, 2016",all,Drunk N' Deadly,"Mordheim : The City of the Damned is a pretty complex turn based squad game where you are managing a warband fighting and looting in the streets of the city of Mordheim.A lot of people will complain the RNG is unfair or rigged due to simply not understanding the mechanics. As this is one of those games that even after a 100+ hours you occasionally will still learn new things about how to best deal with your opponents, how to minimize the effect RNG has on your success and failure.The game is in a similar genre of game to Xcom, though to be fair it has a lot more complexity and stats going on, which can lead to a lot of confusion and frustration for even the most seasoned turn based tactics gamer.This in no way makes the game worse once you get the hang of the game and how it works, it can however lead to a frustrating early experience, especially if you go into the game without understanding how it works to at least some extend.Veterans of the game will consistently have warbands with a 95%+ win rate against the AI, some of us even 99-100% win rate on majority of our warbands, which is a clear indicator that in the end, RNG is not the determining factor majority of the time.Are there times where RNG can completely mess one or two of your dudes? Yes, but you will maybe at most lose one out of a hundred matches against the AI Purely due to RNG, if you are losing more than that? It's cause the player is doing something really wrong.Now don't get me wrong, the game has its flaws, such as a reversed difficulty curve and by this I mean that due to how little control you have with a level 0 to 3 crew and the low amount of income you will have while learning the game, which can definitely make the game hellish difficulty wise the first few warbands you build until you get the hang of it.But take the time to learn the mechanics and build your warband and trust me it will pay off in the end.Should you buy mordheim? It depends, it does take a certain mindset and a lot of patience, in addition to that it requires that you accept your own mistakes as a player. It is a hardcore experience that will take a lot of dedication to master and due to that I can't recommend the game to a more casual crowd of gamers.However if you are in for a challenge, willing to accept blame for your characters horribly dying (not blame RNG) and the dedication to master the mechanics of mordheim? Well go get it already! Cause you will be in for a wild, gut wrenching ride that might just make you the richest warband of the streets of mordheim."
