76561198016997891,Recommended,276810,19166617,"Posted: 19 November, 2015",all,spifomie,"So the game has been released. How does it fare up?Overall pretty well.To make this short, sweet, and lazy: if you fall into any of these catagories, you'll probably find this game worth the price:-fan of the original mordheim tabletop game-fan of warhammer-constant progression marred by varying degrees of crippling injuries suffered in battle-don't mind a bit of RNG goodness-like the idea of being able to customize a warband and watch as they grind themselves into the ground hunting for precious green rocks admist the horrors of a dangerous trap filled battlefield.Did those interest you? if so, you might enjoy this game.however, there are some things to keep in mind:-graphic/animation quality is quite low for a title priced as such, especially when compared to the incredible graphics of also recently released vermintide.-1v1 matches only. No options (balanced or not) for multi-player. Considering how long each match takes, this might be for the best, but still something to mention that the option isn't present whatsoever.-rng injuries/battle system is fun for some, but not fun for others.-not enough customization options to make the warriors truly feel like ""your own"". Presets can be quite annoying to work with.-LOOONGG loading times. even on SSD and cranked up computer.-Occasional multiplayer D-syncs which makes playing contest matches a bit risky.keep in mind, at this point, for those more focused on the narrative, there is a ""contest"" mode which allows injuries and such to take place in multiplayer, but no way to set up leagues, multi-player matches, or other features one might expect when trying to do those old-classic crazy matches like you can when huddled around a mordheim tabletop.for 40 bucks, the quality of the game is a bit low. I recommend it if those bullet points interested you. If they didn't, then perhaps look into vermintide for a AAA production game at a 30 dollar price tag set in the warhammer universe."
