76561198044103214,Not Recommended,276810,27751153,"Posted: 26 November, 2016",all,ksgoldenbadger0,"The reason I would not recommend this game is because of the random number generator the game uses for the various tasks your characters perform.  I am not sure if others have had the problems I have, but at least for me, during each and every mission there would be streaks of terrible luck.  There would be six to seven tests in a row where the ""80%"" or higher chances would fail.  This was not an occasional thing, this was an every mission thing, and almost always took me from having the edge in a mission to either just succeeding or failing miserably.  I played dozens of missions, and these streaks would pop up in every single one.  In addition, though I always equipped my leader with the best parrying weapon and shield combo I could find, I did not make a single parry test the entire time I played, despite there being a ""50%"" or higher chance to block... and again, I will state that I played dozens of missions, each of which my leader would be hit multiple times while attempting to block.I do not mind difficult games, I enjoy a challenge, but this did not feel like a challenge.  This was me being (rightfully) punished for tiny mistakes I made, but then being screwed over by the random number generator when I was doing everything right.  I would make tactically sound decisions only to have them blow up in my face- not just occasionally, but EVERY. SINGLE. MISSION. I. PLAYED.  Again, I am not sure if others have this problem as well, but from my experience this game needs either a re-work of their random number generator or a more realistic statement of the odds on a given action."
