76561198002403505,Recommended,276810,18962575,"Posted: 8 November, 2015",all,Bullrott,"Let me start by saying that I bought this game a week ago, and I now have over 35h played; says a lot!If you are looking for a punishing (hardcore) turn based strategy game with Warhammer setting & lore, chances are you might love this game!There is a small learning curve (however tutorials will greatly help if you take the time to go through them) and controls & mechanics may take a few hours to master, but once you do, the game really becomes fun & immersive!Basically you create a Warband, customize it (for each member you get to choose its weapons, armors, skill points / attributes, spells, etc...) and then fight skirmishes against the AI or players. Shall you emerge victorious from a mission, you'll accumulate xp & loot/gear; however if a soldier falls in battle, he may become permantly injured (suffer from stats reduction).If you take the time to get inot the game, you will get attached to your warband, curse at your monitor when your captain/hero takes a few big hits, and celebrate when you finally overcome the enemy and see him routing.For a long time I have been looking for a PC port of Warhammer tabletop games, and it's finally here!I started playing Mordheim in October 2015 (early release), and I can say that at this point the game is quite polished. Sure, there's is room for improvement, but overall the game is definetly enjoyable in its current state.I cannot wait for offical release, and am keeping my fingers crossed for the addition of new factions. Would definetly love to see some greenskins (orcs & goblins), elves (dark, wood, or high elves) and dwarves!While I acknowledge this game may not be for everyone (its a turn based strategy game), personally I must admit that I've been having a blast!Hoping to see you on the battlefield, and looking forward sending your warband to the hospital xDMy score: 9.5/10Bull"
