76561197991657927,Recommended,276810,21617317,"Posted: 4 March, 2016",all,MrMuse,"So what IS this game exactly? Well it is to Blackguards what the new XCOMs are to the old ones. So it's a 3D tbs. But it's designed to be pretty hardcore from the outset and this actually works because it stops you getting too strong too soon and retains an addictive quality where you just don't want to accept defeat. In this sense, then, it actually has more in common with Blackguards than any other game I can think of. The same moments of feeling absolutely robbed by the RNG and the same crazy difficulty spikes. I can understand why some have downvoted it for this reason because it can be very frustrating and it constantly autosaves so, much like a roguelike, there's no getting around failure with scum saves. I read a few reviews where people criticise the AI but, to be perfectly honest, the fact that you are outnumbered by superior forces 99% of the time means that if the AI were any better you would always be crushed. The warbands are just about different enough to be worth multiple replays and overall it's a very rewarding experience for those who can stick with it.*edit* As of the introduction of the latest DLC warband - The Undead, this game is now more well polished and well rounded than ever. After almost 170 hours of playing, this is, in my opinion, on the shortlist for one of the best games ever made."
,Recommended,276810,19537942,"Posted: 6 December, 2015",all,Yare,"My only complaint is that the success estimates for attack/dodge/parry are not accurate. I'm not harping on the random number generator -what I'm saying is that it's obvious the estimates do not take all modifiers for both parties into account.It's common in Mordheim to miss 5-6 times in a row with a 90% hit chance, or to get smacked 3-4 times in a row by an Impressive even though you're in dodge stance with 95% dodge rate. The odds of these bad runs happening should be one in a hundred, one in a thousand, or worse. But you will see one or two each skirmish at higher level play. It's quite frustrating.Other than that, the game is fantastic. Check out Valkyria Chronicles if you're looking for similar mechanics wrapped up in JRPG window dressing."
