76561197993474708,Recommended,276810,24745958,"Posted: 6 August, 2016",all,Donnerjack,"This is not an easy game. Not a casual game. If you thought the likes of Xenonauts or other micro-management games caused you anxiety and a sense of overwhelmedness, this just ups the quotient.There is no hand-holding in this game. In fact, the tutorials are just as likely to end with you defeated as with a victory. Which is a good thing. It confirms to you just how unforgiving it will be when you actually engage the gameplay. Everything you do is tracked from the word go - the only semi-casual element would be the skirmish mode where you can play free of consequence to your warband. Otherwise, all actions and consequences follow you from the git-go.This is a tough game to recommend. Am I happy to play it? yes. does it feel fun? yes. was it easy to crack the ice that surrounds it like a diamond shell? no. But get that crack and it begins to spread and reveal the gem I hope to continue to find it to be.And while I know this dates me as the less-than-young man I am, a game like this truly makes me pine for the days of game manuals that were hundreds of pages long. A nice heavy book to occupy your mind and time AWAY from the screen and equip you with the tools and skills you will most benefit from when you set to playing.  Just an observation, but I do miss those days.A few more missions in and I must say this is just incredible. The damage/reward system is very crucial to optimizing your experience. upgrading is not easy to come by, but so very pivotal when you have the chance. And the RPG elements of equipment management also lend a very fine touch of color to this fantastic tactical strategy gem.  major thumbs up"
76561198005796162,Recommended,276810,33433604,Posted: 10 July,all,Amokat,"Mordheim is how tactics games should be.Let's be honest and up front here: this game has a few issues. The load times tend to be long, and the RNG and AI combo can be punishing for your characters and your sanity. However, I don't think these problems eclipse the fact that Mordheim is FUN. The different warbands are cool and diverse in playstyle, and loyal to the originial Warhammer universe. The balancing act of in-mission decisions and of managing your warband between missions provides a nice tactical counterpoint - cost/benefit analysis is important at all stages. The pacing of missions allows you to make the measured decisions and careful considerations that a tactics game should require, and the different objectives and conditions throw curveballs left and right; that's how it should be, in my view. If you like a game to challenge you, you got it.Mordheim is HARD, very hard, and combining high difficulty with a single autosave file means decisions (and mistakes) have permanent consequences. It can be discouraging - but if you like games that make you work for it, this is a winner. The payoff for time invested is a very real sense of accomplishment."
