,Recommended,276810,18419375,"Posted: 10 October, 2015",all,aspaceotter,"So I am going to try and be as informative as I possibly can with this game.The game has four factions each one with unique units that can wield and use varieties of armor and weapons. To start the game you are going to choose one of four factions, the choice of faction is crucial to your play style. Once chosen you are going to begin leveling, and yes you level everything, even the poor little meat shields you hide your damage dealers behind. This entire game is based on leveling, accept that fact and youll be perfectly happy with the game. Now the key detail of this game in my eyes is going to be resource management in the warband screen. EVERY MEMBER of your warband must be paid, and you must send wyrdstone to those who request it, miss four shipments and its game over. Inside your camp you can almost fully customize your characters (this is a detail of the game that i want more improvement on) by changing the styles of their gear and equipping them new armor and weapons, also training them over days in spell casting and skill use.now once outside of your warbands camp youll be placed on the campaign screen (the newest update added this finally!). Once on the screen youll be given a variety of missions to choose from, all with varying difficulty and loot. Once you get your warband high enough you will be given an end of act mission. These end of act missions have objectives that must be completed such as placing sanctified hammers on statues, and cleansing the corruption from holy artifacts.The actual gameplay is a turn based strategy format. Units take turns based on their initiation, this is lowered by heavier cumberson items and armor/weapons. In many ways I have found that the weaker glass cannon units go first most of the time, and depending on your faction you may or may not have any of those. Now one thing this games combat does very well is its implication of stances. there are many stances in this game including ambush dodge and parry, being the primary stances. Combat can be very difficult at times because your units move spaces may not get you in a proper postion to attack, and often leads to bottlenecking through doorways or over bridges. Each mission you recieve has a primary objective of killing all enemies or causing them to retreat. Retreat is caused by you forcibly removing morale from an enemy by either surrounding them and causing fear, or the killing of their units. (im not sure about this but it seems like killing enemy heroes and leaders causes a deeper impact on morale)One thing to be wary of is any kind of % chance, as this game is still in Alpha I will go back and change this review as needed but as of now a 78% chance of climbing over a wall seems to have only a 30% success rate, and yes I have tested this by losing over 3 units to trying to climb one wall.All in all this game is amazing, definitely a must have for any warhammer player, and a must try for any strategy enthusiast, this game will punish you through crippling soldiers or even permanent death though. So if you do decide to try it watch for ambushes, and stay away from charging Daemons! Enjoy!"
,Recommended,276810,18428471,"Posted: 11 October, 2015",all,blade413398,after u do a little stuff to make it work its a damn fun game i like it good job with the graphics and the fact u can loot and scavenge for stuff
76561198068984848,Recommended,276810,18443718,"Posted: 12 October, 2015",all,sundownm180,"So far its good, I played this game when it first came out, and was not impressed, no custominzation, no level progres, and unless you chose the upgraded version of your class, you were going to lose alot. I am happy to report that they fixed that, each warband you make feels unique, and you star with a rookie, or later on with the right amount of coin you can be a trained rookie. So what is  the good and the bad?Cons:The AI can be a bit wonky, as in if another is blocking the path to get through, they will just end there turn, did have one funny moment when an ranged AI decided to jump of a 15ft wall, take fall damage and attempted to shoot and miss, felt bad for him.The daughters of Sigmar feel a little op, if you are brand new to this game, this is the faction to avoid in combat, they are the tank/mage group, meaning they can cause lots of damage and take it, now they are fun to use and also I do appreciate they are not visually clad in bikini's as most games I see will do with an all female faction.The Price is a little high in my opion, I bought this when I had more money, for an Early Access I understand they need every cent to make the game good, but you risk scaring people away. In this regard I would say  if a friend bought this, ask to try this game, cause if its not for you, then you will probably come to hate this game.This game has its own lore, but if you are not a Warhammer, fantasy or 40k fan, you may be lost, I would see the Warhammer wiki page, but this is a grim dark fantasy game, meaning its not going to have a happy ending on most days. The story for now is ok, I do enjoy making my own adventure, but there is no cutscenes, (so far), so you dont see a major progresion, they are realeasing Act's as time goes on, so maybe there will be chages.Pros:Its a good warhammer game, visually all the characters are right, the weapons they use is correct, and all the maps feel like you are an a chaos corrupted hell hole.Its fun to see your warband progress over time, and customize them, give them new armor, weapons, skills, so its like xcom except warhammer, and you feel the weight of their deaths.The mission types are fun, for now, mostly its about collecting wyrdstones, and fighting enemy warbands, and if the mission is to hard you can send scouts to find different missions.The engine is not to bad, the game visually is good, gruff, abomination look is what I would expect from a warhammer game. I hope they do add in a faction like Orks/goblins, since all the other factions have a specific reason for being there, it would be a game changer if one was there just to kill everyone, not for chaos or the empire, just for fun.So all in all my fun rating is a 10/10, I love playng this game, but my more professional side says a 7-8/10 it has issues, some parts of the game will feel a bit unfair, like if you have a 95% chance to hit but miss 3 times, and have a dodge of 80% but get hit twice does feel a bit cheap, and if the decrease the price a bit, I would reconmend this game to all my warhammer friends. I did not play the boardgame version of Mordheim but this game has caught my interest. That feeling of conquest is always great and this review may change when its complete, but for now I reconmend this game because for the time being, even though I went into more details about the bad, its still a fun game I just went more into it because I feel that part is for the devs or people who want to see what may turn them away from this game, and weigh it in their own minds, because this is still a a fun game  and I enjoyed it."
