76561197971208698,Recommended,276810,26560804,"Posted: 12 November, 2016",all,Drarz,"Someone finally nailed tabletop gaming.If you played Modheim on the tabletop. Or Warhammer FB/40k. Or D&D. Or any other tactical miniature game on the table you recall hours spend crafting the perfect hero, squad, army. You had dream of how it would perform on the table, visions of fantasy glory. But often the game itself would get bogged down in rules and pitched battles would take hours to complete.The Mordheim successfully captures the enthrawling character/army building process and then pairs it with a very engaging, fluid combat system. You can build, fight, die, and build again several times in one evening. The mechanics are intuitive and easy to grasp but deeply tactical with enough RNG to harken back to those days around the table when a brilliant plan went spectacularly bad or a horrible idea went astonishingly good.I would love to see more races and more units, though there is a very healthy selection of themes, tactics, and strategies available now. And I would love to see a support tournament and league mode, which would further recreate our collective tabletop experience.The bottom line is this: late at night, after my family is asleep and my adult responsibilities are done, I can load up this game and push minis across the most beautiful city of the damned ever assembled. No organization, no preplanned event nights, no massive amount of money and time invested in collecting and painting. How perfect is that?"
