76561198025340157,Recommended,276810,22013057,"Posted: 23 March, 2016",all,Wangtron3000,"This game is a 3D Hardcore, Permadeath, Final Fantasy Tactics. You are encouraged to play slow and tactically. If you rush in your character will die. But I love this game! There are many intense moments, where you don't know if the risk that you took with over extending to pick up a Wyrdstone was worth it or not until the end of the round. Your characters are EXPENDABLE as much as you would love to keep them and in perfect health. If you play cautiously, you will die less, but get less rewards, and vice versa. Sometimes the RNGesus is not in your favor and sometimes it is. A lot of people highlight the horrible moments they had in the game that caused them never play the game again or ALT+F4 the game. I have been there too, but i get sucked right back in after im over it. This game is like Licorice or Cilantro. You either HATE IT or you LOVE IT. Much like the Dark Souls Series. There is a steep learning curve, but once you get past that it's awesome. If you are on the fence, i say buy it, then give it about 3-5 hours, if you love it, keep it, if you hate it, Steam's refund policy is awesome.Welcome to Mordheim............. City of the Damned!"
