76561197975698109,Recommended,276810,29289497,Posted: 15 January,all,LazerShoes,"Initially I wrote a negative review about this game because it spanked me and I ragequit.  I've deleted that review and persisted with the game, read some articles and learned how to play it and I have to say it's a lot of fun.  There's some rich tactical strategy to be had here.This is a game of positioning and attempting to outmaneuver your enemy.  The combat is quite savage and I think a lot of the negative reviews would go away if the developer simply let the player decide what difficulty level they wished to play at, rather than forcing the player into the way they want the game to be played.You will get no easy, normal or hard campaign.  Each mission is rated starting at normal, hard, brutal and deadly.  Right from the get go.  The AI stays about the same but the enemies get massive buffs as the difficulty increases.Of course, you don't have to do these hard missions.  But there are better rewards if you choose to do them.  And it's incredibly satisfying when, either by skill or luck, you win a challenging mission.There's a lot of customization of your warband and it's a lot of fun naming and making your troops into characters.  Your fighters can be injured and a couple of mine are missing arms and one now has a peg leg.  There are definite consequences in this game and no save scumming.  There's no saving at all, its all autosave and you cannot reload.I'd say this is an excellent game, but it's also very hard, there's no doubt about it and if you don't like to lose you'll have to get good if you want to survive the deadly streets of Mordheim."
