,Recommended,276810,25102338,"Posted: 23 August, 2016",all,Disgruntled Peasant,"Whilst its quite unpolished with clunky UI, its an excelent strategy game that manages to be challenging and rewarding.I cannot stress enough that it is VERY challenging, you might get on a winning streak for a while, but one bad loss can leave your veteran soldiers permenently dead or with debilitating wounds.Whilst that sounds frustrating (and is!) it creates a brilliant atmosphere where you have to constantly judge the risk and reward of each mission, often encouraging you to use new recruits as meatshields whilst your elite troops look for safer opportunities to attack.Thankfully the game comes with a progression system so that even if your entire warband gets killed, you will have earned a bunch of bonuses to any new warbands you create which helps the difficulty not feel too opressive.in short:-A challenging game of calculated risk taking, it is not a game of certainties but rather of adapting to misfortune.-Somewhat unpolished, UI is poor and controls are unintuitive.-Fairly repetetive gameplay, there are story missions with unique objectives but the bulk of the game is within familiar streets of the city fighting against roughly equal forces.-consistently creates interesting strategic situations without clear 'best' solutions."
