gs like that and then it boils down to basic attacks. I even have my friend who is a die-hard Warhammer fan and frequently plays and loves all their games, but he actually hates this game and thinks its garbage (I don't know his reasons). Try it if you want, but I'd not recommend it."
76561197980333161,Not Recommended,276810,29849481,Posted: 11 February,all,Brother PaciFist,"Hello, here is my review for Mordheim: city of the damnedPro:Nice and rather unique gameplay for a tactical game, you run in 3rd person view around in the levels. That is rather immersive.Contra:Difficulty and Balance is all over the place. You can do like 10 games a win and then be slaughtered hard without any possible resistance.The start is just too hard. Your warband units are just useless, they can't hit♥♥♥♥♥♥ The enemy units have roughly 50% better stats in every category. My henchmen have like 100 hp the enemy henchmen have 150 in a normal mission, not hard or brutal or even deadly. Some faction like the skaven dish out healthy damage like 60 2 times in row, enough to one hit a lvl 0 henchmen or even hero.Bad Levelscaling:The warband rating raises with every win or levelup of your units. But the combat performance of your men does not rise so fast. So you are outmatched every battle, the sense of progression is just not there. Why even bother with playing the game if you never leave the underdog status. Even the number of enemies is the same as your warband. If you take an impressive with you you will face an enemy impressive. An impressive is a big special unit. The excitement.Tactics, The only way to win battles is numerical superiority. Building tanks or dodgy characters is just luck. You can win but not consistently, having bad luck just destroys your team. So you try to attack a single foe with all of your men and hope that you can kill them piecemeal before the rest of the enemy warband arrives. So the tactical options are verynarrow in the beginning. Later it could open up, but skills cost a fortune. That leads to the next bad point.Economy:You get like 500 gold at the start to equip your warband, but there is not really much to buy in the shops. After each battle you have to treat your fallen wounded warriors or get new men for killed or crippled aka worthless units. That can happen rather quickly. So a small warband that was doing rather fine could be utterly worthless after one battle. I only played like 20 battles until i lost interest. Wound treatment costs like 15 gold per wounded unit. I had many successful missions without any gold income so far. The items found sold for 2 to 5 gold pieces and were really sparse. The wyrdstone collection does not get you much income too. Like 140 for 75 or 380 for 145. But you spent more on warband support und treatment cost then you earn. A really rough start.Difficulty:There are not really difficulty options. You can search for easy missions, but that easy missions are not easy at all. The enemy warband is better in every regard then your units. On hard brutal or deadly missions that gets really out of hand. The enemy units have double the hp, can not be hit at all and have double the damage output then your units. And the difficulty rises automatically with time. Yourwand gets slightly better, even non combat stats rise the warband rating, so your units do not get more efficient but the enemy does.Ranged units are wortless in the beginning. Even when they hit one time a round they do laughable damage. like 15 hp of an enemy unit. In melee they die quickly. Against some warbands that dont use ranged units often you gimp yourself by taking units with you.There is no saving option for your warband. Hours of progress can be lost in the blink of an eye.The story campaign missions were too hard, had no chance with a fresh warband in it. You are expected to grind random skirmishes forever to get a maxed out team that is able to do the campaign missions. So there was no story at all for me only random missions.I played only some matches but this game seems only for expert players or cheaters, the start is so roughly and seems impossible. Hard games like Dark souls are a walk in the park compared to this atrocity. If you like to be hit repeately and punished then this game is perfect for you. If you like random dice rolls that are rigged against you, if you like untouchable enemy units, that you have next to zero hit chance against, if you like AI getting high advantages in every category that is. Everyone else should avoid it like hell. Not fun at all for me.Thanks for reading have a nice day."
76561198053169798,Recommended,276810,31488567,Posted: 1 May,all,Morne,"Am addicted to this game. Its turn based like x-com but instead of a grid, your movement is based on distance, which is refreshing change. The game can be really punishing at times, characters can end up with injuries, lost limbs, eyes ect or even die. Can be frustrating if you have invested time and gold in leveling them up but personally i think its a great mechanic, it makes the game intense. There are exhibition matches though without negative consequences but you dont gain loot or exp. Would of liked to have seen a bit more options for customizating the characters apearance but theres lots of skill and spell customisation for them. There is alot of RNG but you can lessen/improve its effect by leveling up and buying passives. So far ave played 200+ hours and its still holding my interest. Pity the devs have moved onto a new game, would of liked to see more dlc, saying that am looking forward to the new game as well."
76561198092629637,Recommended,276810,28380274,"Posted: 14 December, 2016",all,1mahkt,"The ""Dark Souls"" of Tactics GamesFirst lets clear up the ""RNG"" conspiracy all of the negative reviews are focusing on. When you see 67% for a hit that is what your chance to land a blow is. IF you roll that check and IF you get your 67% your opponent WILL THEN roll their Dodge/Block chance. That is not taken into account into the % to hit chance you see. Settle down and do some research before crying about the difficulty.With that said this is a great game, it will make you go rage mode but will keep you coming back for more if you truely enjoy tactics games. This game requires that you have overwhelmingly solid tactics making use of choke points etc. You need to keep a pretty deep roster because you will lose guys in a fight. You will need lots of trial and error but that makes a win more rewarding, and unlike some games when your guy gets ""knocked out"" theres a chance he will make it in the end, albeit with possibly one less arm.This game has hundreds of hours in it if you want to invest in trying out all of the different factions. I haven't even beat the game yet and have over 80 hours. I recommend this game to anyone who can do the math and do not to those who scream RNG and hit the refund button."
