,Recommended,276810,24756694,"Posted: 7 August, 2016",all,Birb,"I don't do many reviews but I thought i would put something for this game.(I have played quite a few hours on this with my offline PC)(Edit - Spell check lives again so corrected a lot of errors... Sadly was on an odd day)Personally i thought this was a good although very difficult game when i started, but i found despite the few issues and UI the game was actually quite good.If you are looking for another casual turn based game where you can just pick some classes and tank up then I would recommend avoiding this game. Every mistake you make will come back an haunt you at a later date including avoiding some side objectives,I think it would be easier if i gave a basic description of the pros and cons for this game...Camera: The camera is a 3rd person camera that locks onto the unit you are meant to be moving that turn, Doesn't allow free roaming with the camera and makes seeing around corners and in buildings a little more difficult when trying to avoid ambushes.Movement: This caught me off guard at first.. Using the standard movement keys WASD to navigate was a bit odd for a turn based game but once I figured out the blue circles were something akin to movement areas, you would only lose a movement point when changing to a different ring giving you free movement within your Movement points.Actions: This i found a little off at first but every action has a reaction.. Firing a gun means it needs you to use a reload action, gives you arm fatigue for the rest of the turn lowering accuracy.  Climbing walls needs at the jump points Isn't always guaranteed with a chance of a sprain if you are very unlucky ect. Usually it is best to prepare for the consequences for most actions.UI: I agree with most people... It is a little clunky and not the best.. But when you look past most of its appearance you mostly use Q & E to change action instead of a menu. Regardless it shows everything you need.Ok now for a simple list:Pros:On High graphics settings it looks goodAI is hard and sometimes unforgiving (Well good in my opinion)Soundtrack is fittingOpen maps in most levelsExcellent customizationConsequences for loosing affect appearance of unitsRandomly generated map placementsSome replay abilityUnlocks persist through multiple play throughWays to deal with enemy vary based on your preferred tacticsCons:AI is hard but can predict how they act based on the game modeVery few game modesUI is a bit clunkyMaps look a bit samish even if they are randomly generatedOn low graphics looks appalling compared to most modern gamesDon't always get chance to loot stuffThe game is hard, fun but at times frustrating when it goes from bad to worse. Not always the end of the world but makes progression harder.  Worth it if you like difficult games that seek to destroy you in as many ways as you can.. until you figure out AI tactics but even then still easy to die.I'd give this game a 7 out of 10.. Despite its flaws it has some merit and room to improve."
