76561197965020920,Recommended,276810,19332611,"Posted: 28 November, 2015",all,Ragnek,"A TLDR at the bottom of this review to summarise my points.I really enjoy this game, though it is anything but a 'pick up and play' game for when you have ten minutes to kill. The graphics are beautiful and illustrate the lush environments of a seedy and damned city. The gameplay is challenging from the outset and learning curve (if you ignore the tutorials) can be steep. I chose to play through as Skaven, and haven't tried the other races as yet, so my opinions may be invalid or void with regards to their gameplay. The customisation of characters is adequate, it's not an integral part of the game, and seems to be purely asthetic, though it is a nice touch, as is the injuries, for example; if a character maims a hand, their hand on the character model is mangled.The story missions, character progression and warband management are all solid, on the whole, the game is well made and fun, whilst having a high level of strategic gameplay. However... and this is my only gripe about the game thus far, the load times are ridiculous! I have a high end machine, and yet sometimes I can go away boil the kettle, make a cup of tea or coffee and return and it still hasn't finished loading the map. This is the main reason I have yet to try any of the online features. Also, it is annoying when the voice overs from the mission and the narrator fight it out trying to talk over eachother, resulting in a garbled mess of voices and leaving you to read the mission objectives etc... for vital information you need.TLDR:+graphics+voice acting+ gameplay+story+ challenging- load times- voices overlappingOn the whole a great game, but not for the impatient."
