76561198285621115,Recommended,276810,34078501,Posted: 7 August,all,Jake,"I love this game.If it is your kind of game, you will understand me.You level up your heroes until they are super tanky, or can hit hard or just stand on a rooftop and play sniper - but with one bad roll of the dice it's all gone. In my opinion, anyone who complains about the game's randomness being ""unfair"" has never played a similar boardgame based on dice. They ARE unfair! You always have a chance to fail miserably and make your charakter loose an arm.It is a hard game. No question. The tutorials offer you an insight on the game mechanics, but there's still a lot to learn. You may fail with your first hero, but you'll know what to do with the next one. And honestly - I have a smuggler with only one leg and she's still running around and killing stuff. So don't worry too much about that.Just give it time. Don't give up if it doesn't work for you when you play your first game!Many reviews complain about the long loading times and the AI's turns being to long. Just think of the boardgame and its setup. It takes much much longer, and your opponent might take a lot of time thinking as well. The same happens to you here.I'd love to play this game online against human opponents, but I already like it against the AI. I played it over 100 hours and there's still stuff for me to find out, so I'm excited to play a lot more!Long story short: If you like strategy games that don't give you anything for granted but only if you work hard for it - pick this game up! If you don't, then don't."
76561198032796319,Recommended,276810,34058759,Posted: 6 August,all,Apollo Densin,"Overall this game falls into the catagory of highly difficult but highly rewarding. You need to think really tactically, using buildings and choke points to your advantage, if you can lure a foe to hit you and get them stuck in a door, but keep enough room avalibe for your hidden unit behind the wall to join in the fight, you will have an extreme advantage.The game has a high difficulty curve, but unlike games like Dark souls it is less on pressing buttons at the right time and skill, and more on tactics. RNG will not be your friend, but in turn will not be the friend of the enemy at times as well.I would like to see some more warbands, although we would be treading into the unofficial warbands most likely from here on out. special hero units should be a lot cheaper as well, but this is just going to fall under the dlc craze most games have now adays.Overall I reccomend the game, if on the condition that it is a hard game to play and you will lose. But it is one of those games that I will keep coming back to after being frustrated with it for awhile."
