,Not Recommended,276810,29779560,Posted: 8 February,all,Karn,"Saw a sale going on now, felt compelled to give a review to let fellow consumers know some flaws in this game. But the final decision still lies with you if you're comfortable with the potential enjoyable aspects of the game.Haven't played this for the past 6 months, obviously due to some gripes about the game. The game is not well suited for mainstream audience, as it is very technical. And the tutorial only covers the very basics, which leaves you feeling confused as you start to play the campaigns. The game was implemented from the board game perspective, so it does feel quite confusing sometimes.Example, your unit is going to target an enemy unit. Let's leave  out the RNG mechanics aspect 1st. Let's say i have a 85% chance to hit. That chance to hit is based on your unit stats as the 1st calculation. It has not taken into account the enemy's dodge stats and other situational aspects that may affect the final calculation.I cannot see what is the point of porting the boardgame to video gaming if the developers does not make use of computing to make the final calculation for the player, then for the player to make a risk/reward decision based on the available info given to him.The final straw came for me as i mistakenly upgraded another skill instead of the one i wanted. i can't remember the skill name, but they were both identical and listed one beneath the other. and with the all white and tiny font size, it takes amazing eye vision to squint and carefully read. Needless to say, there is no option to undo a honest mistake.There are a few other aspects which i don't like, but i'm not able to remember clearly which mechanics."
