76561198009847378,Not Recommended,276810,31949852,Posted: 25 May,all,How Zany,"I've put up my own series of guides and a play through on  youtube for the Skaven faction and I had invested a lot of hours in this game and I kept thinking maybe this game can be great, I mean otherwise why would I put so much effort into making an entire youtube channel for this game?The thing is, this game is very unique in that it is basically a tabletop strategy game that was turned into a computer game making it more accessible to the more ""casual"" players. It has the potential of being almost as popular as chess. BUT the devs didn't understand this potential and didn't understand how to unlock it.The Good:-This is a very challenging strategy game that involves  a solid understanding of Strategy concepts and players who crave a deeper experience or who have read and know how to apply The Art of War and/or have military background would enjoy this game.-This game is exciting and draws inspiration from a fun franchise.The Bad:-This game does not have a lot of players who play and due to the decisions made by the developers this game is likely going to only be played by the most die hard fans.-The developers only focus on graphics and it took several months after release for them to fix the random teleport/rubberbanding issues which would cause your units to teleport randomly around the map which will likely get them killed via being put too close to the enemy by being too separated from friendly units.-This game does not really have a smart AI and therefore once you do have a good solid grasp of how to be strategic or use positioning to cheese the AI you will be able to pull off victories without any loss of units every single game and this makes the single player very dry and boring since once you've reached that level of understanding (by following simple rules like 1. Damage comes from surrounding enemy units with multiple units of your own, not giving each individual warrior high damage... 2. Reduce the enemy's damage by taking them out at chokepoints if facing superior numbers so that doorways become key real estate to control. 3. Pulling your low health units back and switching to ranged weapons if any makes your units be able to carry on fighting even if they are low on health and in this way reduce their risk of dying while still getting usefulness out of them.)The Ugly:- The way the Devs made this game, the game is extremely punishing in that if you lose a unit in combat they might die or get a permanent injury that will make them useless and all those hours of upgrading them is wasted. Then there's the fact that if you lose a match your entire team will take damage and possibly die. There is no way to prevent this.- The game's brutality is further compounded by the fact that multiplayer is the same exact thing where if you play multiplayer your team will also DIE if you lose and even if you win any unit that was knocked out will likely die or take permanent damage. There is a ""no deaths/penalties"" mode in multiplayer but because of the overall brutality of this game where you can't save so you can't reload, nobody plays multiplayer anymore.- The no saving, every decision is final, permadeath, devs only care about releasing DLC's and upgrading graphics part of this game makes this game prohibitive for new players who want to play and also makes this game exceptionally hard to get into because unless you are a seasoned pro at strategy games (like myself), you WILL struggle and cry bloody tears when your favorite units die in horrible ways because of a simple misclick that you made and there's no way you can take it back."
