76561198054829096,Not Recommended,276810,23907260,"Posted: 28 June, 2016",all,dougatosb,"NOTE: My hours played should be far more than shows because I've mostly played this game offline.I REALLY wanted to like this game, and for periods I would have quite a bit of fun with it.  It mixes several things I really like: (1) Turn-based combat; (2) good graphics; and (3) a 3D Map.  But I'm about to uninstall.My primary issue is COMBAT:- You want victories to be as clean as possible, meaning that none of your troops get put out of action (lose all their HP).  That's fine, but the ""strategy"" required to avoid such ruins the game.- The RNG of whether you (or an enemy) hits or misses a swing is far too important.  I don't mind an unforgiving game (where its very possible to lose characters or die) but when the unforgiving element is tied heavily to RNG, that's a problem.- The enemy often has more (or stronger) troops that you do.  They will swarm on you really quickly once they find you.  So if you go out and try to collect loot on the map (fun) you expose your troops to getting pounced upon and dying (not fun).  The best tactic is often to ignore loot and set up a very defensive position and simply wait until the enemy finds you (not fun).- Some maps force your units to be split apart from each other, either randomly or by choice.  In any event, its quite frequent for some of your troops to be separated near an enemy.  Once they jump on you, you can't really effectively run away.I think those are enough points to give you my general impression."
