76561198021581283,Not Recommended,276810,28335730,"Posted: 12 December, 2016",all,herparchist,"Mordheim is a merger between two of my favorite things, tactical strategy and warhammer fantasy.  Mordheim should be the game that I spend 100+ hours playing, and mucho dinero buying all the DLC. Instead it is infuriating beyond belief.My complaints first:Tactical game? -- has no functional top down view, no functional grid, nothing to help chart pathways, lay ambushes, plan charges, nothing. Ambushes often times do not trigger, for reasons unknown to me. Sometimes my warband can charge engaged opponents, sometimes not, seems completely random. I've found my warband stuck in poor situations too often, due to not being able to gauge distances, etc...Inventory-- is a total joke. Small items do not stack, WTF???? Bob loots 3 coins from a body. Bob gets 5 coins from a chest. Bob has 8 coins, right. No Bob has 3 inventory slots and two of them are occupied by 3 coins and 5 coins. Now Bob previously picked up a total of 27 coins. These 27 coins all fit in one inventory slot, but either Bob is too slow to put all his coins in one slot, or...Same thing with wyrdstones. Small fragments take the same space as clusters, which are 10 x the size? You also can't equip anything you pick up. The helmet you just picked up, which you have a place for, on your head, nope no putting it there, that'll have to wait till after the mission.Gameplay-- is slow, with unnecessary animations. Opposing warbands are really aggressive, their only tactic is to swarm. Quest goals are sometimes vague and can take forever to figure out, or the quest will just randomly end, regardless of wether you are able to complete the objectives, or not.And your typical gather wyrdstone quest, goes like this. 3-5 rounds of exploring, looting, gathering. You get noticed by the other warband. They swarm your warband. One leader/hero or another falls. Morale check. Quest over. And this happens over and over again.RNG-- Game uses rng which can get stuck, causing your warband to suffer, sometimes permanent damage. I just finished a match where the roll was 90 for four consecutive attacks. I lost the objective, due to my hero falling to a zombie with 10 wounds left. Seriously, the zombie has time to destroy my hero, while two other henchmen miss all their attacks. Hero falls, zombie loots the token I took from the other warbands hero, I finally get a shot in on the zombie, morale check and quest over. No objective for you.My compliments:Warband develpoment -- Customization on every member of the warband. You can tweak each member of your warband to make them specific, dynami, and unique. There are almost too many customization choices available, which means you can really spend time and geak out.Landscape-- Mordheim is Warhammer fantasy to a T. It's brutal, trap filled, landscape in ruin. Basically Warhammer fantasy.Mechanics-- Not fully a plus in my book, but I do like that the warband can do maneuvers and attacks. Different maneuvers use movement points, attacks use offensive points, etc...I don't know if any of the issues I have with the game will ever be fixed, or if anyone with the ability to mod or fix some of this stuff will. I hope that happens. Like I said, Mordheim should be the game that occupies way too much of my life, except that it isn't."
