76561198006632534,Not Recommended,276810,21635925,"Posted: 4 March, 2016",all,Urake,"This game is too hard.  The original Mordheim (and Necromunda etc like it) were tabletop games where both sides were humans and most importantly 'Used the same dice'.  Here the computer has one loaded set against yours.  Before people cry 'RNG' I have seen that in other games - even games based on other tabletop games by Games Workshop, and at least its generally fair even if you have a bad game sometimes.  But here when my character misses 3 '90% hits' in a row, and his one hits with 3 '60% hits' in a row - and it happens almost every game - I call that cheating not 'RNG'.  When this happens in 'every battle' then it goes beyond a joke, and so I have decided to uninstall this game today.  A shame really - I enjoyed the seeming difficulty to start with.  But there a difference between a difficult game (which I enjoy) and a cheating opponent (which I do not) - and there are better ways for a developer to make a game hard than loaded dice!  Not even remotely recommended - 2/10"
