76561198022754544,Recommended,276810,19593561,"Posted: 9 December, 2015",all,chaosguy,"A good TBS game!   You move a Warhammer-style squad through the ruins of a city in search of comet fragments.  4 different factions with 4 somewhat different play-styles give it decent variety.  AI is generally predictable, prioritizing loot over tactical advantage, but will react quickly if you make a mis-step, and also makes a point of prioritizing & hunting down near beaten warriors of your squad if you leave them exposed.MP is much more of a nail-biter challenge, as each player scouts for the other and tries to bring more force of arms to the point of conflict before the other player.  One-on-one duels between squad units tend to be RNG affairs, which make a lot of the strategy about tactically manuevering your opponent into an ambush where you can bring the hammer of sigmar down on them with the full weight of your squad."
76561198051605111,Recommended,276810,19595205,"Posted: 9 December, 2015",all,Jos,"This is a rough tough game and I love it.+ It doesn't baby you like ♥♥♥♥♥ console games.  When you make mistakes you will be punished (sometimes severely) permanently.  BUT it has a decent set of tutorial missions to ease you in and get you and your warband on your way.+ If you are a  squad-level strategy fan you'll probably like it.  It's similar to XCOM, Blood Bowl, and Space Hulk Ascension if you've played any of those.+ It's original.  I love that the devs took risks on this and I think it paid off.+ The graphics are certainly not AAA, but they did a good job of making you feel like you're roaming the twisted streets of the city of the damned.There are some downsides for sure:- Currently loading screens are almost 1 min, and I suspect it has quite a few memory leaks.  Hopefully this will improve with patches.- The 3rd person persepective really detracts from the strategy nature of the game.  It's very difficult to navigate your team around the multi-level streets without constantly flicking over to the map.  I wish they'd built the game more around top-down perspective.  Having said this I can see why they chose to get you down into the streets where the action is.- Alot of the bonuses are marginal.  I find this frustrating.  2% here, some other useless skill there.  When your men get 'killed', often they either suffer some marginal penalty, or get one so severe they are finished.- The AI is pretty good compared to many games, but has some pretty serious flaws.  Hopefully this will improve with time."
