76561198040296113,Not Recommended,276810,20135165,"Posted: 30 December, 2015",all,Kaloyanov,"Just to preface with 'gaming experience' in the 'Warhammer' setting...1. Warhammer 40k fan (Rogue Trader) - shows me age...2. Warmaster Fan - shows I enjoyed more than just the flashy Space Marine or the gritty Black Orc...Really wanted this to be something good - as in 'a successful port'.Yea...So, as a port its not bad.Pros:It's a port of the mini gameCons:Create warband.  Warband does so-so.  Warband instakilled in match against a basic opponent that just rolls them....aaaaand....not enough starting money to reliably rebuild.  And, this is only day two?If more starting money was provided to rebuild a constant battle of warbad attrition = no thanks.The balance is off plain and simple.Should you OP through the game = no.Should you have to struggle through a game = yes.Should you be bent over a barrel every single game = no.There really needs to be a flat hand versus a thumbs up and down in the rating section because a thumbs down really isn't fair - to be honest...As an IT person what the devs did was actually really cool...it's the balance that's way off; and, not in the building but in the battles.  Yes, yes, yes - the setting is supposed to be brutal but I should not be missing 85% chance hits four times in a row in matches that are right next to each other.  That should be something of a statistical outlier.Would I recommend this game - no.And, that really pains me to say that as I understand the business model and the 'need to eat'.Balance the math behind the scene a bit and get back to me.Other than that - bravo devs!"
