76561197988978984,Recommended,276810,31659638,Posted: 9 May,all,Wrayden,"Quick comments (so not really a review): If you enjoy tabletop miniature gaming with a little RPG thrown in, then Mordeim will satisfy those needs on your kitchen table.  If you want all that and the kitchen sink, um, a worthy pc version, then Mordheim is reeking with atmosphere and brings the same gameplay that you would find on the tabletop.As long as you understand that the game is emulating the best aspects of tabletop gaming while taking advantage of the PC platform, then you will enjoy the hybrid type game play.  If not, then you might as well go back to Rainbow Six (nothing wrong with Rainbow Six, just saying).There is a sharp learning curve, but once you learn it, you will immersive yourself building a war band in the most difficult and competitive environments.  This game is not for the faint of heart or those players who want easy wins.  Your games will get better, because you learn to be a better player.  You learn to minimize risky tactics to maximize your long-term strategy.Mordheim – unforgiving in its game play; rewards richly in the long term."
