76561198035269442,Not Recommended,276810,23143499,"Posted: 22 May, 2016",all,Learned26,"The regular campaign missions have a number of small glitches/errors and can feel quite arbitrary. Said errors sometimes hamper you, sometimes the AI. It says something that for a while Sisters of Sigmar gangs caused me grief because I would have to fight their impressive warriors, whereas I normally relied on them being stuck in doors. Similarly, it helps to pretend certain other glitches are actually intentional - your best warrior spawns in a room with no exits? He obviously fell victim to a trap or similar etc etc (Incidentally, that happens quites rarely, and i'm not bitter, honest). Annoyingly, everytime an update has come out it seems to have brought at least one new glitch with it, but generally it's a pretty shiny game so i'll be quiet on that.What makes me unreasonably angry and is going to lead to me walking away for a while (I'll probably come back, I'm a sucker, but i don't guarantee it) tends to be the story missions. As a rule of thumb I don't write reviews but, while I've never felt so euphoric I've been tempted to write a positive review for Mordheim, every other story mission has made me consider throwing the computer out the window and dancing around the ashes. Why? Sometimes it's the same glitches combined with the extra difficulty and the fact that failure nets you dead and mutilated party members but no material award. Mostly it's the extra special glitches they roll out just for the story missions - key items that don't spawn, or they don't register that the character has them, or the character is killed and no-one else can pick it up. I could go on, but the item issue is the one that crops up most often. I also take issue with not being to check who is carrying what, but that would just be convenient and I can at least overcome that with pen and paper.As a final note, I will say that the glitches really are peculiarly evenhanded. In a previous storymission, tasked with setting free 2 sisters of sigmar to aid me in defeating an all powerful magic used protected from outside harm, said magic user  attempted a spell and was instant killed by a miscast about five minutes in. But just like I don't really want to beat other gangs because their impressive warrior gets confused by corners, I don't really want the occasional plot mission handed to me on a plate to counterbalance all the ones that are exercises in futility."
