76561198034609086,Recommended,276810,20443518,"Posted: 10 January, 2016",all,Scuds Radio,"Do not be fooled by the trailer like I was, this game is way better than they let on. Watch a few lets plays on youtube. Know that there is robust RPG game here, and not some flashy lore filler, bord game adaptation.The game is VERY luck based, but you will soon learn and adapt. Also you will lose in some way, no matter what. Consider that, as the rage builds from a failed dodge roll. That is the aim of the game, how you adapt to loss, how well you recover. Even the narator asks, ""How will you die today?"" Your playstyle will depend on these decisions.Then there is the AI... just know that it's not like facing a player. They will head strait to you like they have a psychic link with you, the kind only true lovers share. This really dose break game immersion, as you play you will know that charging one character after another into the other tearm's warband is a bad idea and that is what the AI does. Some times it does catch you offgaurd, but most of the time it just forces you into a single strategy and can get dull.I havn't played multiplayer YET. When i try no matches show up so... I imagine it's like Blood Bowl. It's where you face off against an oppenent that only wants to cause long term damage to your team, ignoring the task at hand, only to cause grievence to you personnally by making your team unplayable after said match. I'm not really into that.The campain is hard, even with the derpy AI. Try to go in way above the recomended point value.All in all this game is great, watching your team grow from the good and bad. I may not have a story behind that characters missing eye, or why exactly that character is missing an arm, but uh... the next battle will be better?9/10"
