76561198133256047,Recommended,276810,25353493,"Posted: 4 September, 2016",all,AVChimecho,Mordheim: City of the Damned is overall a fun game but it requires a very patient and forgiving player sometimes to enjoy it. Originally you have to build up your numbers slowly from 5 members in your warband (which I supported when first playing the game but by the time I made my 20th Warband it felt very restrictive and tedious) to a maximum of 9. The game can become rather repetetive after completing all the story missions with a Warband but before then it is varied and interesting for the most part. There are amusing visual and technical glitches which are relatively harmless (such as being unable to go down a set of normal stairs etc.) but there are also rare glitches which cause warbands at rank 10 to all suffer injuries due to a forced game shutdown (this having occured to a friend of mine's Skavens and he was not very happy to say the least). Never did I feel that one of my casualties was unavoidable and was caused rather by my poor decision making and replacing the units is not that hard in general so I feel the game is usually fair and not that difficult. Learning unit's strategies and combos is a thoroughly enjoyable part of the game that gives it some replayability. However one problem I have with the game is the number of warbands. There are originally 4 to choose from (with an additional one that can be bought as DLC to bring it to 5) and even though their styles are different I would obviously enjoy more Warbands
