76561197995724407,Recommended,276810,19746200,"Posted: 17 December, 2015",all,Wyoming,"Great game. A quality TBS, but not for the feint-hearted. This game does not pull any punches, if you are easily frustrated by RNG sometimes going bad on you then you should probably steer clear for your heart's sake!For everyone else though this game offers a great and intuitive combat system, built on the in-depth character customisation system, which ensures the combat gets more involved as you continue to grow your warband. All your characters have enormous potential for growth and customisation, no red shirts here.The different warbands all play very differently from each other, which unique strengths and weaknesses that need to be played to if you want to last long on harder difficulties. This makes for some some nice variety in gameplay and enhances the replayability of the game.Only two major downsides:1) The predictability of the AI, after a couple dozen hours you will be able to fairly accurately predict how the AI will react to things, and accordingly it becomes easy to manipulate and destroy them by constantly swarming them.2) The load times. This game has the worst load times of any game I've played in the last decade, no exaggeration. We're talking 5mins+ to load a level on an SSD."
