,Recommended,276810,19839533,"Posted: 22 December, 2015",all,Black Sam Bellamy,"So good. Nothing quite like taking a bunch of poorly-trained characters ranging from henchmen to mighty heroes and indomitable impressives, and turning them into an unstoppable band of grizzled veterans. You can grow strangely attached to some of your warriors (the ones who survive countless skirmishes), and the chance that it can all go wrong due to factors outside of your direct control (dice-rolls) keeps things suspenseful. If a warrior goes down during a fight they can either recover, die, or suffer from injuries ranging from funny quirks to complete catastrophes. The more you play the better you get at mitigating potential disaster, especially when playing against the predictable AI. After the tutorials and a few battles you tend to get the hang of it pretty quickly, so I'd say the learning curve is totally manageable. The missions are split into ""Normal, Hard, Brutal, and Deadly"" categories so you can always up the ante to even the field a little. I've played for a while already and feel like I'm still scratching the surface of character building and learning the ins-and-outs of each unit. For me, this game came out of nowhere and has been one of the best gaming surprises of the year. Highly recommended!"
