76561198029300088,Not Recommended,276810,23873405,"Posted: 27 June, 2016",all,yenkin2001,"Update:  I have asked for a refund, this game is just to frustrating and even wins feel like losses.  Sorry I really wanted to like this game.  I am hoping that Steam will allow the refund as I am over the 2 hour limit, but this game takes longer than that just to figure out how to play.  It was not that much so if they don't refund no biggie, but would rather spend my money on something else.Update: I am stilling leaning Yes after a few more scenarios, however this game is hard, very hard. My Warband got decimated in a Burtal Campaign that kept sending in reinforcements and eventually do to attrition I lost because I was missing one of the key objectives.  I had everything else could not find that last objective.  The problem with that is the high cost of medical treatment and then paying  your Warband.  Can't say I was pleased with that. But it is a stiff learning curve so after a bit of research I now know to stay away from these brutal types for a few more levels.After Stating another Warband and a better  understanding of what I am doing, I have made it a bit further then with my original group.  I will need more time with it yet to see if it is a sustainable game or will my mouse go through the computer screen in frustration.  I found myself a few times yelling expletives at the screen, no game really brings out that emotion.  So while we are in the ""yes"" I will say the metered moved towards ""no"",Early review, I think this is worthwhile at this point as I believe those who purchase this game should be aware that the learning curve just to get started is very steep.  If you are looking for a game you can just drop right in and play, stop, drop and roll on by, this is not the game you are looking for.  The tutorial system is a mess; they would benefit greatly by creating the tutorial as a chain rather than pick a topic and jump in.  This is one of those games that is not hard to play, but it is difficult to master.As for the play of the game it took a few tries to actually win the first mission without losing my entire Warband, there is no lead in to the Campaign, which gives you a few light and fluffy engagements to win. It is kill or be killed.  You learn very quickly that if you separate a member of a Warband the AI is relentless and will gang up quickly and single a member out.  But the good news is that tactic works for you as well.  You can also exploit the environment to some extent with LOS, and Height advantages.Game play is not to bad once you get over the initial OMG what the heck am I doing here.  As I stated before took me three tries before I won a match and only lost one instead of the entire band.  Losses in this game are just that, a member of your Warband dies, he is dead.  He may not die, and in one case he lost a limb, which may or may not be causation to be fired, but you still pay his healthcare.There are game guides out there, I am just looking at those know, as I think a few tries and you can start to put together some questions on the mechanics.  This genre is specific to either the Warhammer crowd, or for those who like very micro managed man to man tactical games.  Was the game worth the money, that remains to be seen, but I will be playing it again as I like this type of game, though would have liked it a whole lot more with an easy lead in to teach the game mechanics.Since there is no middle ground here at steam I picked thumbs up.  More to come…"
