76561198007427346,Recommended,276810,29202930,Posted: 12 January,all,Flambeau200061,"All in all, the game is fun, with a high replayability. You can quickly get attached to your warband characters and will feel woefully sorry if one of your highlevel soldiers looses an arm or a leg or gets killed on a mission. The six warband all have their distinctive features and play differently enough to use them all. Levelling options give you a great number of choices - better than XCOM2. Character customization is o.k. but  might be improved (more head or at least hat types) and a little less varied than in XCOM2.The game itself is fair enough, you can choose between ""Normal"", ""Hard"", ""Brutal"" and ""Deadly"" mission types. So far I have only attempted ""Normal"" missions, as - depending on your starting position and your opponents - even these may be challenging at times. Story missions so far are o.k. as long as you can avoid mistakes like not keeping your warband together. Beware that the game runs always in ""Ironman mode"", there is no savescumming and when your characters die or get maimed, they stay dead or crippled. Perhaps the introduction of some exit points on the maps would be a good idea. At the moment you can only ""abandon"" a mission  at the cost of injuries to all party members or end the mission by failing a party morale check - difficult if you have high leadership stats, as that means you will have to have almost all your high ranking characters out of action before party morale falls below the critical value.There could be more maps though. However the existing maps are big and as starting positions and weather conditions (day, night, fog) vary it doesn't get too boring. But two or three more maps would be nice.Hopefully the devs keep adding content to this game. It's much better than ""Darkest Dungeon"" and almost on par with XCOM2."
