76561198030824996,Not Recommended,276810,18642512,"Posted: 23 October, 2015",all,towerwizard,"This is my second edit to this review. The game now has an auto-save feature, although I have not tested it due to my rage uninstall at the strange decisions of the developers earlier, and the fact that Fallout 4 has now hit the market.This game fuses the usually divided muliplayer and single player game modes into a single unity. This poor design decision led to the idea of punishing every user who exited the game prematurely, using alt-F4 or other means such as crashes, even when only playing against the AI. The above mentioned auto save has now apparently fixed this problem, however.The game uses mandatory iron man mode, though, due to the needs of the multiplayer community of having a fair game. Casual single player lovers are thus ignored by the developers. There is Kes' way to play, or play another game, as I have done (Fallout 4 is out, remember?). So make a mistake, or roll unlucklily, or get hit by a clever or lucky attack, and many hours of progress can go away. I doubt I will play his game again...----------Now, read, if you care, the below, earlier, review. I won't remove it.----------I started following this game more than a year ago. Back then, it wasn't for me, because Mordheim is all about the progression of warbands in my opining. Now, however, since they added progression, it is my mostly played game, and it is still in Early Access!This game is a shining example of how an Early Access game should be produced:1. The developer listens to the community, reads the forums, and responds, not only in writing, but in the game. Some of the updates have been as a direct result of player feedback.2. The updates are wonderful. Their contents are extensive and the rate of updates are regular (at least one per week).3. They do their very best at developing the balance withing the game in a logical manner. Add something, wait for feedback, and if needed tweak it. Add something else, repeat. It is like watching some one paint a painting; each stroke with the brush is based on the previous, and the picture emerges ever more beautifully.Sure, I don't agree on everything. Some decisions seems strange to me, like the way the warband teleports around the city, and how they are perfectly safe in their ""virtual"" home base in between missions.The game itself is loads of fun, though! It is really hard, and sometimes frustrating, since it is in a permanent state of Hardcore (permanent injuries and death may happen to characters, and NO saving and reloading). I really like this game. And it is not even out of Early Access yet! It will be both a sad and a happy day when the game is released, because then the wonderful updates will stop.TL;DR: A bad design decision killed a fun and challenging and brilliant game for me that is otherwise well worth its selling price!"
