76561197972450743,Not Recommended,276810,22076411,"Posted: 26 March, 2016",all,faurester,"This is a game I really wanted to like as I played the game in my University days with figs and dice. I had found memories and hoped that the fun would be translated to the PC version. However, this was not the case. The deployment is terrible. I have played more games than I can count that found all my men spread to the nine winds and the enemy all clustered together. So needless to say they took out a good 25%-50% of my forces before I could rally my men together and defend.Another major frustration is that with no save capability you lose a character that you have worked hard to develop over 30+ games and one good roll that is it for him. I like that the game is hard and so trying again is fun but you are not able to try again since there is no saving a battle. I do not understand how a game developer still thinks that the vast majority of gamers do not want the option to restart from a save position. XCOM2 does it better by setting an Iron Man mode if you wish to play with no saves and dying being permanent. That is fine for them and I love the game. If Mordheim wish this then it should be placed on the game description that you have no save, restarts with your group and damage and death is permanent.This is a game for entertainment and leisure. I am like hard games and a challenge is good but all the games I know let you try again and learn and change outcomes. Very few of the people I know find it fun to die and then that is that. Far too random for that. There is some strategy but sometimes no matter how the odds are in your favour all your 90+ strikes will miss and the 60+ from the enemy will land time and time again. This gets to be very annoying and you end up no giving a crap about your men since they will die no matter what.To the developer, add game modes and saves and maybe you will find more client buying your game. I for one will no longer play or recommend the 