76561198075367957,Recommended,276810,31994377,Posted: 27 May,all,Elaborate,"There are great things and awful things about this game, with that said I do enjoy it a lot. I should also tell you that I am a player of the tabletop game and have been for 15 years or so.Great things:- The general ""feel"" of the game is spot on. Atmosphere, design and sound are perfect!- Warband management is really fun and well made.- The story missions are challenging and for the most part fun(I will elaborate on this in ""awful things"")- The warbands that exist are well made and have good distinctive units.Awful things:- The AI is really stupid, which breaks immersion and makes the missions less challenging at times.- Cult of the Possessed campaign act 2 is really badly designed and balanced. This really need to be adressed by the devs, as for now it's not worth it to play the possessed.- Constant reinforcements from the enemy in story missions, this is just a bad design-choice in all games in my opinion.- Badly needs more warbands and I really hope this game isn't abandoned by the devs. We want more content!- Some mission modes are just plain stupid and happens way too often. With this I mean missions where you get randomly deployed on the map. This would be fine if it where once in a while but it feels like every other mission is like this. It makes mobility overpowered, as you heavy armor slow guys won't get to fights in time and won't do♥♥♥♥♥♥ For the same reason Skaven is broken in these missions as they can run the entire map in one turn more or less.So there are quite a lot of things I don't like in this game but they can be somewhat adressed in future patches. Just hope this game isnt abandoned.Overall a good game that i enjoy playing, but has a few kinks that annoys the hell out of me. I think the game is more fun for people who have played the table top game as there are A LOT of mechanics to learn if you don't have a basic understanding of them.So I do recommend it but it's not perfect."
76561198154029976,Recommended,276810,32065171,Posted: 30 May,all,The 9th,"Absolutely awesome turn based game in the Warhammer universe!Let's start with the cons though.The graphics aren't something great, but that won't even bother you as you play this game, since it will keep you on your toes and deliver a great experience each time you play it.It has a limited amount of maps to choose from. Still, not something that downgrades it that much.AND of course the curious way that probability works... Meaning, you have a wizard casting a spell with 95% success chance... 2 times fail and the 3rd one he explodes and dies... WTF? Or if you attack an enemy with a 80% chance then you miss 3 times in a row only for him to hit you with a 30% chance. Oh well...BUT!This game is absolutely well done, since as it warns you from the start you have to make the best out of the worst situation and as soon as you master the way you ought to play in tough fights or when gathering wyrdstones, it becomes an awesome experience. The campaign arcs for each faction are well done (especially the maps, I remember getting stuck in a cursed library with the witchhunter team) and the story keeps you interested.You will upgrade your team slowly and they WILL accumulate injuries which you will see on your enemies as well. For example a missing arm, leg etc.The multiplayer isn't anything special, but it gives you and a friend a chance to either kill eachother brutally or have a fun match with no repercussions.Overall this game is a fine addition to the whole turn based universe of Warhammer and along with its great atmosphere it delivers a very challenging playthrough for each and every faction you choose.8/10!"
