76561198006100475,Recommended,276810,26325362,"Posted: 30 October, 2016",all,Shids,"I have played Mordheim since before it was released, and then I am talking about Games Workshop miniature tabletop game, so I have followed the Mordheim franchise since they posted a trail version in an old White Dwarf magazine.So when I first saw this game on Alpha, it was an instant buy for me. Sadly, my first experiences of the game made me doubt if that was money well spent. So after having tested that beta for about half an hour I shut down and decided not to poke it before it was released. And now, almost a year after it left its alpha and beta stage, I wonder why I ever doubted Mordheim back then.So what do I think of the game? I love it! It's a wonderful, turnbased stratergy game with some light RPG elements to it as it includes a few story missions for each faction.Are the rule systems the same? Does the computer game use six-sided dice? Does character progression work the same way? The skills? All the various heroes and henchmen? Spells? Items? NO! No, they are not the same.Does the computer game capture the essence of the original miniature tabletop game...? <Insert curseword> YES! Yes, it certainly does and more.So no, you won't be able to play the exact same game here that you would if you play with your miniatures, and my opinion is that it's a good thing for once. This game offers you, in some ways, more and different options that you lack when you play with your models.The only true downsides with the game is that the core game only had four races (they have added two more with dlc now - which I don't mind, but others do), grinding missions might get a little repetative if done for hours and hours without a break and some seem to think the game is hard, but I generally have never had a problem with it, except maybe the first mission at times. Just.. don't be afraid of someone dying! Except if it is your leader, then you might have problems.."
76561197981603123,Recommended,276810,26327477,"Posted: 30 October, 2016",all,rabbittruns,"This game is many things... it is thoughtful, deep, steeped with lore from one of the most amazing fantasy settings ever created since it is warhammer, among many things.. But i think the most important part of this game, and what makes it different from almost every other game out there, is the emotional context.there are NO saves other than the one you have. EVERY time you choose a mission and your crew, there is a very real possibility for failure and death. I have succeeded on the hardest ""brutal"" missions and wiped on the normal rated ones. The game is so emotional because there is a sense of accomplishment and loss that isn't present in other games simply because other games give you the option of iron man mode which most never take, and this one just forces it upon you because that is life in warhammer. Brutal, short, and only the strongest survive and flourish.If you want a complex, deep, immersive experience where you must consider every move, because each move can mean triumph or disaster, then get this game. I've raged quit screamed and yelled at the RNG but i think it is actually pretty fair. It doesn't cheat as some say, it is just what it is. If you have played xcom or any other rng heavy product you will understand. The only difference with this game is that on several unlucky rolls in a row you may lose a character you have spent months developing, and there is no scum saving like xcom. You have to deal with the consequences of a harsh existence, which is what the WARHAMMER universe is all about.So if anyone cares i absolutely recommend this game. There are many things i would like to see implemented as far as the campaign goes and not getting pretty much the mirror image of youur warband to face, and maybe revenge missions where you get to face the band that wiped you previously, but maybe they will come and there will be more diversity in the campaign. either way if you are on the fence, do yourself a favor and try it! especially for the sale price it is now you cant beat it."
