76561198060659972,Not Recommended,276810,19644704,"Posted: 11 December, 2015",all,jasque101478,"It is with a heavy heart that I write this review. I bought into this game while it was still just out of alpha, and in that raw state, I could easily see the potential. I loved the tabletop version of Mordheim, but when people complained that this was not that game (which was a true statement,) I could defend it on the grounds that this was a different good game, as long as the devs fixed a few problems with it.The biggest offenders during early beta were:Poor RNGPoor deploymentUnbalanced warband ratings (the AI always had higher ratings, sometimes significantly so,)An impossible midgame (survival rate at warband level 5 was practically 0.)Navigation difficulty (can't see the map except with a largely useless overhead view.)I watched as the devs tweaked and tweaked. I continued to defend the game because they were trying to fix it. Eventually, I left the game for a while. I figured I would come back closer to release to see how it had changed. I did not get back to it until tonight, a little under a month after release.I jumped back in and discovered some very beautiful new splash screens! The visuals had all gotten a touchup, including my warband models. Things were looking up!Then I started the gameplay. My warband rating was 440. My opponent's rating (on regular difficulty) was 500, a 13% difference. Still, I could do this! It would be challenging, but what game worth its salt isn't? I started to play. Within 2 turns, my warband (which had been randomly deployed despite the fact that I wanted to manually deploy them) were being 2v1'ed. I had 2 henchmen that I could not get to the skirmishes because I could not find the right set of stairs. My engaged warriors did about 10% damage to the opponents' healthbars, who then one-shotted one character and stunned the other. (This was in the second round of the game, first round of combat mind you. I did not engage the enemy models because I knew I needed to gang up - I just could not find my way around the map (or even find a way to escape the enemy's close proximity.)By turn 3 I had lost 2 units, one of whom was my hero, and routed. I then had both die in the after-action report.I know that a good game should be challenging, but this level of stupidity is just...well.I cannot recommend this game. I really want to, to validate my choice to buy in during beta, but in the interest of integrity, my advice is don't. Just don't. Find some other challenging game, one where the RNG doesn't kill you instantly, one where you can find your way around the levels, one where you do not lose because two warriors randomly die after only your first battle.Find some other challenging game. Find a good game. Not this one."
