76561198037243515,Recommended,276810,31657198,Posted: 9 May,all,GoD p@RTicle,"I have played this game since it launched. And I loved it. Its a squad based game, in the way X-COM is a squad based game. Every week (of game time) you can go out on a mission. Every mission has its own obejctives. The game play though is much different from X-COM as there is no cover system. But the environments are complex as in there is plenty of scope to sneak up on opponents or be surprised by an ambush etc.This game is not for the faint of heart. They actually reduced the difficulty after everyone was complaining that it was too difficult. I have seen the a lot of reviews of frustrated souls who have not recommended this game and their only grouse is that it is too difficult. Thats because you have to be very careful about picking your missions and also you will fail some missions. Believe me you can beat the game once you learn the mechanics. The guys with the bad reviews just couldnt figure it out.CODM has an extensive and challenging single player campaign. In fact I havent really ever played a multiplayer match and my guess is it will be fun. There is a skirmish mode for you to go one on one against your friend using one of the factions that are in the game. Each faction is fairly different from each other as expected of a multiplayer strategy game.The graphics are not the best, yeah maybe things coulc be improved, yet the gameplay is awesome and I highly recommend it to people who like strategy and roleplaying games."
