76561198004430537,Not Recommended,276810,19222314,"Posted: 22 November, 2015",all,Spire,"This is an odd review. The game plays fair, but the mechanics are not for the faint of heart. The quick anwser is that I would not recommend it to other's as it's particularly niche and unforgiving. Frankly if this fits someone's niche perfectly I doubt they even will look at the reviews, however I can see casual players being burned.My beefs:i) Pacing is slow. This includes playing/fighting on the map, but also the time investment needed to progress is quite large. Almost into the grindy realm.ii) Unforgiving. You can literally spend hours honing your character, picking spells and skills, spending alot of your gold on them, only to have a rough few hits lead to an injury that truncates that character.iii) Playstyle becomes defensive. Largely due to the previous point, your effort to save your character's from any hit means you constantly are trying to swamp any resistance, which can lead to long games adjusting for position which just exasterbates the drain on enjoyment.iv) Repetative. The leveling system is beautifully detailed, however the large number of games you play to level your characters tend to not diverge much from one to the other. This game is more enjoyable in short sessions as long one's tend to become monatonous.v) Frustrating. The game is successful at getting you to grow attached to your main characters, however there is some maps that put you in a difficult position that often leads to a rout of your men as you fight to stay alive. When such things happen, it is needlessly frustrating as the punishment onthe loss can be quite huge, from loss of all your hardearned weapons, injuries dimishing the characters, to permanent deaths of your characters. Frankly this game is not for the faint of heart, nor the easily discouraged.So personally I'm the typical audience for this game, and I'd pass it off as a 6/10 for other's of a similar mindset. However I'd mark it just 4/10 for the general player. As the points above will have a much larger impact on their playtime."
