ial 80% rolls.Its nothing new really. We've seen all of the above in X-COM, Blood Bowl, Xenonauts... However, in those games when you won a mission you really felt like you accomplished something. I know I did. Got some alien bodies, ship, saved country from leaving the council, whatever. You got that crucial dose of happines that allowed you to survive all the pain you suffered.In Mordheim: City of the Damned your victories are not worth a damn and defeats are absolutely brutal."
