76561198033038612,Not Recommended,276810,23088740,"Posted: 19 May, 2016",all,Whooplaah,"This is not a game. It is a stress and disappointment simulator. There are no tactics - only luck. There is no fun to be had, but by the time you realize that you will have too many hours of play* to get your money back from Steam.*Play is used very loosely here. You will spend more time looking at load screens and waiting for the computer take its turn than you will spend actually doing anything. I would often get up and leave my computer while 'playing' this game because a 5 minute wait for my turn bored me.The game often freezes up during the computer's turn, and the developers don't seem to respond to bug reports. After 3 patches the issue persists. The worst part about the bugs is that you have to force-close the game, and the game thinks you are cheating, and so when you load that save your characters all get permanent stat penalties (which is part of the game).The controls are slow and not designed for computer. You can't click, you can't mouse over for information, you have to cycle through disorganized lists.There are four warbands to choose from but they are not balanced. No matter which one you pick the result is the same: there is one enemy you will always win against, and one enemy you will always loose against.The game is not tactical. If you go up against the warband that your warband is weak against you simply cannot win. If your character takes any amount of damage they may end up with a permanent disfigurement (loosing an arm and not being able to use weapons, loosing a leg and not being able to equip armor, loosing stats, loosing skills, etc). Your chance to deal damage to an enemy will hover around 50%, but even with 95% chance to hit I've had characters miss 5 times in a row and then die. You don't get control over troop deployment. You don't get to choose what type of mission you go on or what the objectives are. You can't see the whole map, and even what you can see is grainy and hard to decipher. When characters enter melee you cannot have them retreat - they must win the melee or die.There are warbands designed for stealth, and there are character classes designed for stealth, but you can only win by killing every enemy - so any character that is not a fighter is pointless. There are characters locked behind a pay wall (DLC they say) but you will have to fight them even when playing single-player, and good luck doing that without the paid DLC to counter them.The single most annoying part of the game is how your characters get punished as you play regardless of win/loose. Did you win the encounter? That's good. But did any of your characters take even 1 damage during the encounter? Yes? Then lets see what disfigurement they get! Turns out your archer lost an arm and can't use bows any more, your fighter lost a leg and can't use armor any more, and your mage took a permanent -5 to intelligence and can't use some of their skills until they level up. Congratulations on winning!"
