76561198049327388,Not Recommended,276810,19243542,"Posted: 23 November, 2015",all,Exavour,"I am going to start by saying that I LOVE tactical turn based games. I also happen to love the warhammer and Mordheim universe. However this game does not, by any means live up to the standards of an acceptable game. I would call it an ""unforgiving"" waste of development time.The good:-The game is graphically beautiful, the animations and textures are great.-Customization is great. You can really create your own war band how you want down to the color and style of armor, names and even re name the war band.-Tactically speaking this game is great. You can do a lot with what you are given.The bad:-Unforgiving.....This game is geared so hard in the favor of the AI that you can't even progress to mid game. The AI knows exactly where you are and how to own you even on the missions that are supposed to be easy.-The injury system is neat but as soon as you recieve an injury on one of your units you have to wait, which delays the time it takes to collect your next stone shipment OR you can hire a new unit to replace them. However, how are you supposed to replace a new unit without selling stone? The answer: you dont.-Your units can die off forever. Thats right, your units can literally die forever, after putting so much time and effort in to a units training there is always a chance they are simply gone.Final thoughts:Do not purchase this game. I wanted and tried so hard to enjoy myself but after trying all warbands at least twice I found that the game was simply created by devs that wanted to be passive winners. That is completely unaccepatble. I, being a long time fan and player of tactical turn based games, was never able to progress past the fourth day. The game makes it so that if you obtain an injury you snowball in to a campaign end, which is followed by a game over.Waste of time and money. Please invest in another game."
