76561198076543436,Not Recommended,276810,21855833,"Posted: 15 March, 2016",all,Kwisatz Haderach,"Let's start this off by saying I like this game, I may play it in the future if the DLC coming out for it looks good and they fix some of the balance problems.Let's start with the good and the great.-Level designGood, the custom maps are great and the random maps are good except when the occasional glitch happens.-EnviromentGreat, mutated corpses blowing bubbles of blood, giant mutated bodies suspending the roof of a tower, captures the atmosphere of Mordheim.-ManagementReally enjoyable management making and customizing a warband is great fun.-RPG elementsAlso great, in depth, with lots of build options, if the game was more balanced and less decided with a coin toss I could see myself spending hours making builds.On to the negatives.-RNGThe RNG is not right, this has been echoed and repeated by almost everyone, there are less then 20 people I have talked to who can defend the RNG.You can test it yourself, get CoP there leader gets a spell with 85% to succeed. Cast it a hundred times, realize that it only works HALF THE TIME. Casting chance has no modifiers, int doesn't increase it, armor and weapon enchants doesn't increase it either.Its the best way to test RNG.-Implementation of the RNG.This is my second problem, lets say I'm deluded, I'm just a bad player who makes bad rolls scapegoats. Even with the RNG working as it should the prevelance of it is unbearable.Its random when you get a shipment, you can fulfill the shipment just to have once come in the very next day, usually demanding 50 pnds more.Secondly the difficulty of the missions you go on AND the deployment is also random, so you can have 10 days to fulfill a shipment only to have awful rolls that makes it so 6/10 days you have are up against tough or brutal missions all with the chance for your group to be scattered.Which means you will end up in a house with one of your units getting gangbanged before you ever get a chance to move.Mutations are random as well which is fine MUTATIONS SHOULD BE RANDOM, however mutations should not be the saem for EVERY MUTANT.The first Mutant you have excess to has 5 points in ballistic while only 3 in melee.However you are almost gauranteed to get an arm mutation making any ranged weapons unusable so why the hell do we have a mutant that is your only hero option in the beginning with 2 extra points that could be anywhere else except ballistic?The game is full of stuff like this but more on that later.Ultimately with the RNG you will find yourself ♥♥♥♥ed regardless of how well you play, I have lost one match ONE! However I still often restart with a new warband because of being forced into a bad spot by the RNG.For example I have had my leader unit roll Wrath of Tzeentech TWICE in two matches, both on casting WoD and wearing a blue amulet to avoid this.First ended with a light wound rest for two days, the other a near death experience which takes 5 days.My shipment was in 7 days so I had only two days to make the shipment.So whatever I have only a couple more clusters to deliver to make my shipment.So I check the missions, I have the choice of Brutal and Tough missions all with scattered deployment for one side or both sides.With only two days I decide I have to take on so I choose the Tough mission, and surprise surprise my luck gets two of my units basically sorrounded by enemies that get taken out before their turns because of their lower initiave.Which is the point I uninstalled the game.-BalanceGood god the balance is so poorly figured out no wonder multiplayer is dead.Skaven for example are king, they get 3 meters extra movement, which means they can outrange your charges and ambushes even when you have Bullcharge the AI still gets to ambush or charge you on even, you cannot do this.CoP is the weakest group as they are based entirely on RNG and have weirdly built heroes.I already brought up the weird mutant with pointless points in ballistic.Now let me bring up the possessed, absolutely worthless unit, Fear checks are almost always passed by the AI meaning he rarely gets the buff that would make him usefull.He has awful dodge unless points are sunk into it which gimps him in other ways. He is incredibly squishy, only clothing allowed.He has incredibly low DPS, only two attacks on start because he is always dual wielding thanks to bracers/mutations only which means he is always going to cost another OP for an attack.LOSING AN ARM MAKES HIM BETTER, honestly, if he gets his arm chopped off he gets a bonus in dodge, initiave bonus and can make three hits a turn.So in summary to squishy to tank, not enough DPS to be a glass cannon.-NPC handicapsThese are the worst.Skaven which should be a squishy race with high movement is now a terror because the NPC get a large chunk of extra health often given more health then your own units!Their leadership will also rival yours regardless of what your focusing on.It completely skews the feeling of progression.How am I a high leadership warband when EVERY warband has higher leadership regardless of stats invested?Why do I invest into alertness when my units can't ever break ahead of the enemies initiave?You will never have the option for Easy missions, Normal missions is you still facing enemies with higher stats, health, leadership and initiave.In summary.I'm at a loss with this game, I really like its mechanics, I really like how it plays.However the poor balance that hasn't been fixed, the dead multiplayer, the boosted NPC enemies, the constant RNG ♥♥♥♥ery.When I sit down and begin a match while the game loads I just think to myself, why don't I just flip a coin and leave it at that?"
