76561198073125756,Not Recommended,276810,29007011,Posted: 4 January,all,Explo-blazer,"So, what about Mordheim - City of the Damned ?I would not recommend this game to anyone, except an hardcore suicidal masochist, it's a total waste of time, energy, and money !As a fan of Warhammer lore and tabletop games, and of games like Valkyria Chronicles and XCOM, i thought i would enjoy Mordheim as much as possible.Well, no. In fact, imagine a game where EVERYTHING (and when I say everyhting, I mean it) is determined by RNG. From the smallest jump to the strongest charge, every action is determined by a roll between 1 and 100, with a percentage of success.However, in Mordheim, the RNG is biased (if you look others reviews and Mordheim general discussions threads you'll see that almost everybody agree on this point). The developpers wanted to make an ULTRA hard game... and they failed.Mordheim is beyond hard or any difficulty you can imagine, it is designed to make you lose, whatever you do.You can try to adapt tactics and builds, learn maps and skills, play as safe as possible, if the RNG decides that you lose your WHOLE progess (generally dozens of hours) at this battle, trust me you'll lose everything at this battle, and you'll have to start again from scratch.Let me explain : AI's enemy units have huge buffs, even on the lowest difficulty, and the RNG works in their favor. When it says that you, as a player, have 80% hit chances (as an exemple) you'll see that you will never approach the 80% hits if you look at all your rolls. On the otherside, an AI unit with 60% hits chances will almost never miss.These two points combined, whatever you plan to do, you are forced to lose your warband at a point (after of course tryharding it for 30+ hours).This game is beyond difficulty and punitivity. It's just stupid and nonsensical.Another point to not recommend this game at all is the community. There are 2 kinds of people : The new players/the kind ones that are struggling to enjoy this game, most of them leaving it after losing another warband and 50 hours of wasted time due to 0.000001% set of circumstances that happen regularly in Mordheim ; and the 5% old veterans of the game, with 1000+ hours on it, and 10 warbands max level and full purple stuff. These guys will tell you anytime you ask for a bit of help to enjoy/understand the game things like : ""You suck, L2P noob and then come back."" , ""This game is too easy for me, you shouldn't have any problems unless you suck."" and their best argue : ""I have nor problem with my full min-maxed warbands so there is no problem in the game."" And the worst is that they aren't trolling at all, they are dead serious...Btw, graphics are cool, loading times are long, lore isn't respected and DLC are expensive. This game should still be an open Beta, it's full of bugs.Don't buy it ;)"
