,Recommended,276810,13944903,"Posted: 11 January, 2015",all,Delthanesh,"I generally despise early access titles, from a pragmatic point of view and a philosophical view. That being said, Mordheim is an incredible game, especially in this early version. Allowing multiplayer skirmish and warband items management makes this more functional than many other full games.The High Points:-AAA Graphics and Terrain. This team is one of the few that actually gets the central aspect of cover in a WH game.-Skaven and Sisters of Battle. Not since dawn of war has there been a focus on allowing multiple races, and not just the ones that make GW the most money. I hope they expand to Undead, but having these two factions in early access is huge.-Good Tactical elements, bringing the core ruleset to life. There are a lot of GW games that are not worthy of the name, but Mordheim is a shining Paragon of what a good WH game can bring to video gamers.-Blending AAA Third Person movement with a tactical game. This is one of my favorite things, and i would love to see more AAA Strategy games take this and modernize the RTS genre. One of the worst things is that the RTS Genre hasn't really improved over time. This isn't technically an RTS and more of a Tactical game, but the point is it is an innovative style.-The possibilities: This game has HUGE potential, and I pray dearly to Sigmar that they will follow through and get the support they need and dont rush this.The low points:-Its early access. The better parts of leveling up your warband has yet to come, but if implemented fully, it will be amazing. That being said, I don't really have faith in gaming companies, and I hope they can deliver.-Only 3 races and 4 planned as far as i know. I would love to see all the races being implemented, even if quality does trump quantity.-Camera issues when attacking. Pretty annoying but not game breaking. It is immersion breaking though.-Not sure if they can manage to implement all the features that will truly make it Mordheim but its on a roll right now.-Not for pure action junkies. It is for tactical and strategy junkies. Warhammer is a cult phenomenon, and they have yet to come out with a title that competes with most AAA titles like CoD, Mass Effect, etc.Overall, if you like tactical games and warhammer, get this even in early access it is fun. Probably not worth the money until warband management and levelling is in play, though. I have faith in this title and you should too. Unless we are proven wrong."
