76561197982148163,Recommended,276810,13204855,"Posted: 2 December, 2014",all,Bravesteel,"NEW REVIEW:  Many of the camera problems, I am happy to say, have been eliminated in the current updates.  The campaign is here and it looks like it will be a lot of fun.  The game garners a resounding ""YES"" from me now as I actually feel like the game is playable in its current state.  The only comment I would like to pass on to the developers is that the lack of a complete tutorial places the new player in front of an overwhelming amount of choices and options.  I believe a comprehensive tutorial that isn't just a text box would benefit this game greatly.  Warhammer and Mordheim fans, you won't be disappointed.PAST REVIEW: I will say that for Mordheim: City of the Damned captures the feel of its namesake very well, providing a gritty skirmish experience set in the Warhammer world.  However no amount of ""feel"" or ""essence"" can cover up the fact that this game is obviously still very, very, VERY much still in Early Access.  The constant shifting of camera views, the clipping of the camera into random objects during combat ""cut scenes"" and inability to simply have an overhead view where I can control my warband kept me from completely enjoying the game.  Die hard Warhammer fans will enjoy the scenery and the little comments about Chaos in the loading screens, but the average gamer will not find much to thrill.  I appreciate that this is Early Access, but I believe that there is such a thing as too early of an Early Access.  The game overall garners a ""No"" vote from me, and I feel like I'd have to wait for a Mordheim: Chaos Edition to truly knock out all of the bugs.  Personally: a dissappointing purchase."
