76561198094203045,Recommended,276810,20521258,"Posted: 14 January, 2016",all,First&Only,"Mordheim: City Of The DamnedBased on the table-top game from Games Workshop. Turn based, stats based character development, Morale Tests etcThis game is very addictive and has loads of fun to offer. It is also very hard and challenging to begin with (do not expect a difficulty option to start your game). You need to play smart, be cautious and apply some forethought or tactics to your style of gameplay. Towards the endgame things become easier due to character development and your own game experience. Be warned - you can still lose and suffer for it!You will find yourself frustrated and believe the 'die' are always cast against you but this is not the case - this is Mordheim. You win and lose, its how you come back that makes the game have more to offer.4 Warbands are available to start the game - Mercenaries (Human), Skaven, Possessed and Sisterr of Sigmar. Perhaps more will become avaialble as time passes. Each faction has its own SIngle player campaign missions to complete as well as random battle encounters and missions for you to choose from, your overall goal being to keep your faction sponsor happy anf make timely Wyrdstone deliveries in the correct quantity. (You scavange these in mission whilst fighting off the enemy warband).Next you have the whole mulitplayer aspect to the game. Play against real people and experience a real thinking and cunning oppenent as oppossed to game AI. All the while you can gain XP and still level up to use in the SP campaign.Downsides to the game - people say it looks or feels rushed from EA to full release because the graphics are not perfect, if you zoom in and look around you can cut into characters' heads and walls will get sliced off partially. Visually the environment is very eerie and gloomy - well replicated Mordheim there. Yet there is no fine detail and polish. The characters clones, limited base models and are only cusromisable to a degree and can easily all end up looking drab and too similar.There are also a lot of RNG complaints but again you have to make the odds favour you through attacking clever and using numbers where you can to force all alone tests and ensure you can stack attacks and debuffs etc.It wasnt until my third warband that i grasped it and had a little luck go my way and i took them all the way to level 10 overall. Stick to Normal and Hard Missions and pick your tougher fights carefully to give a better chance.Your choices in Mordheim are permanent. Death is eternal.Dare you enter the City Of The Damned?"
