,Recommended,276810,20839864,"Posted: 29 January, 2016",all,Dead3eD,"Be prepared to learn as Mordheim demands quite a bit of attention. You'll want to rush in, but to master the basics I'd highly recommend you play all four tutorials - which took me a vigours two hours. The advantage of playing the tutorials is that it gaves you the chance to dip your toes into the fighting styles of each race. Following those you can learn about how various menus worked, setting up the characters, and so on.Do not tread lightly in regards to the campaign - the world of Mordheim is not forgiving. Be sure of your tactics as one wrong mistake can lead to your defeat. Characters wounded in battle risk X number of days and gold for recover. Units who are ""out of action"" are in danger of being permanently removed from the game. This is hardcore and not for the temperamental, forget reloading if you mess up. Every single action is accounted for.Hopefully more races are in the works (presumably costly DLC). Visually stunning, with a soundtrack to complement. Even with all the tutorials, it can be difficult using the menus. When the loading screens appear, go make yourself a cup of tea/coffee... seriously. If you are serious about your fantasy turn by turn fighting games then you must try this!"
