76561198012838998,Recommended,276810,21728807,"Posted: 9 March, 2016",all,Srab23厄,"A truly excellent game with its flaws. The foundation is set and it's a very solid one. You manage a warband in the city of Mordheim, where a nasty warpstone comet has fallen. This comet has ruined the city and scattered precious warpstone all over it, and your warband has the task of retrieving as much as it can. However, your warband is not the only, and you will face other warbands in skirimishes while gathering as much warpstone as your men can carry.This is a stratergy game with permanent injuries and fatalities to your men. You may select from four different races when creating a warband; Imperial, Skaven, Chaos and Sisters of sigmar. Each has their unique types of warriors and heroes giving you some options in your play styles. My current favotire being the Chaos, or as the particular cult is called: ''Cult of the possessed'', because of their random mutations, which is a unique feature to them.The combat offers a random factor and a lot of stratergy to put the odds in your favor. Archers are at a disadvantage when close to enemies and heavy armor offers you passive damage reduction but slows you down without proper training, for example. I find that the best stratergy is to move your squad in a group to hopefully find some stray enemies and gang up on them, since there are major penalties for fighting alone against two or more enemies. Some maps, however, scatters both your and your enemies squad to mix up your stratergies, and walking in a group is not the most efficient way of collecting precious warpstone.The game would be a solid 10/10 for me if it was better polished (which I think the developers are working on, slowly) and more content. The animations are also a big complaint for me, and almost every chaos unit has the exact same head with just different headgear to set them apart. Four races is not enough, and three of them are human based warband which is not a very exotic race to me. However, this game is still an excellent choice for anyone whos up for a fairly highpaced turn based stratergy game with permanent consequences to your actions. And I think the game will only get better as more patches and DLC are released.Buy this game to suport the creators in improving it into a 10/10 experience!I currently give it an 8/10, it is an excellent foundation and setting, but with some minor clunkyness and a lack of content."
76561198018668216,Recommended,276810,21831054,"Posted: 14 March, 2016",all,Waldir,"Since this games release a lot has changed and for the better.  The RNG and been fixed ALOT and seems much more realistic (no longer miss 6 times in a row with 90%+ chance to hit),  The shipments are much easier to complete in the time given, and load times are no longer 10 minutes.  While all these things seem like they made the game easy mode, the challenge is still real.  You can not make moves without thinking it through, or you will be punished.  Your warband will be rushed if you are not careful and injuries and death are still a threat and make you consider a restart.  If you played this game and stop or asked for a refund I promise you all the things you hated about it are gone or changed.  All that being said I would still not get the game at full price, I would still get it when its on a sale. 10$ off or more, i would 100% reccomend this game if you are a fan or new to the warhammer universe.  A fan or new to the Tactical genre of games (such as x com)  Its a great game to spend a couple hours a day.  I continue to look forward to the patches and dlc they release to further improve the game."
