76561198009419490,Not Recommended,276810,19593368,"Posted: 9 December, 2015",all,Dave_B,"I love the idea of this game, turn-based tactical combat with ability to level up your team with RPG-like skills and statistics in a fantasy setting. Closest comparison I can think of is Valkyrie Chronicles which I played through several times on the PS3 and absolutely loved. While I am still enjoying playing the game, I just can't recommend it for most people due to the following issues:1) Load times and wait times.  As of writing this, with 52 hours ""played"", I've probably spent 15-20 of those hours just waiting... on either loading or waiting on enemy moves/turns. 2+ minutes just to load each mission, and then more time waiting on enemy moves during each mission. And this is on a solid gaming rig (GTX970/skylake i7/SSD).2) Lack of variety in objectives, and penalties for winning ""too fast"". Only 3 bonus objectives in non-campaign missions (gather green stones, kill specific opponents, or capture the flag). But if you don't delay winning until, for example, you run the captured flag all the way back to your wagon, no bonus.3) Very limited number of unique campaign missions, have to spend more time grinding non-campaign missions to collect green stones and levelling than in the more interesting campaign missions. Only 8 campaign missions to ""win"" with a particular race/faction, although replaying as one of the different factions gives a different set of 8 campaign missions.4) AI / bugs. Enemies blocking portals and not moving, or standing / stuck on scenery and not engaging are both annoying and breaking any sense of immersion.5) No story cutscenes, just a narrator reading chapter text. Story scenes really made Valkyrie Chronicles much more appealing as you came to understand and like the characters you were playing.But despite these problems, I'm still playing after 52 hours, so for me personally I've gotten my moneys worth."
