76561198006514037,Recommended,276810,21772311,"Posted: 11 March, 2016",all,warpvyper,"It is a turnbased, Squad based, Tactical Role Player set in the Fantasy/Pre industrial Era of Warhammer.ProsChallengingMeaningful StrategyMeaningful Character BuildingRich EnvironmentCaptures essence of tabletop gamesCons3 mission types4 maps4 factionsNot for the weak mindeda few Clunky game mechanics (looting/targeting)It is actually a really good game for what it was designed to be. It tells your right at the main menu ""Mordheim was designed to be a hardcore experience"" I think it accomplishes this very well.It is hard, it is suppose to be. Your hard earned soldiers are going to die and going to get hurt, and you will be sad. It gets easier as you learn more tactics and your charactera get stronger, but it never becomes trivial. I think this is what makes it so enjoyable. So many games today are easy and formulaic, but in this game you learn and adapt or die.Before I try and convince you to dedicate the time needed to fully enjoy this game, let me tell you my only major criticisms. Once you do figure out how to be boss, and your characters are stronger you tend to use your soldiers in specific ways over and over again for only 3 major mission types, ""gather, kill and steal"" on seemingly 2 or 3 maps. Some of the targeting and looting mechanics require very specific positioning which is just stupid, but you learn how to deal with it....eventually.It is still a very rewarding process despite its flaws, and even once you are da'boss it is still challenging and tactical because if you do not play to your designed strengths you will not do well. Additionally, there needs to be more factions. Right now there are 4 factions (Skaven, Chaos, Empire and Sisters of Sigmar). I think 4 is an appropiate starting number for the rich experience it provides, but I want more. I really hope more factions are available.I will gladly and eagerly purchase them.It was designed around playing a tabletop miniatures game and again captures this feeling very well. I find the combat to be intense, the strategies to be very broad and in depth. Your troop positioning, skills, spells, and equipment really matter. Most importanly though, is the character building. You will grow attached to your characters, and will live/experience game of throne moments when they die, lol.Environment and graphics capture the ""hardcore"" dungeon feel of the warhammer universe. The animations are well done really bringing your characters to life despite being turned based. There is enough gore to keep it realistic too. I anticipate a couple hundred hours of playtime, more with DLC.BottomLine: Buy it if you like challenges and turnbased gameplay, anticipate a learning curve."
