,Not Recommended,276810,24055788,"Posted: 3 July, 2016",all,Patches,"I decided to pick the game up again after refunding my original purchase... They had fixed my main complaints about the game, but it's still buggy. I've had a few instances where I had to force-quit the game and reload due to characters getting stuck in their actions (which becomes a serious problem if the game map won't load up again).The AI is pretty awful and all too often you'll find them running into a wall every turn.The game is ironman mode only, so if you can't load a battle, you'll have to suffer a complete defeat just to load the warband. This is usually a game ender as your warband will be injured (which is costly and the units are unusable).EDIT:After more playtime, my advice is to stick to XCOM... Better yet, grab the Long War mod for XCOM. This game is a bit too buggy (crashes, corrupted saves, deadlocks) and it's lacking in content. You'll play the same levels and the same enemies, it'll never get better as you progress. Sure, there's the new Witch Hunter warband... but it doesn't feel that different from the other warbands. The levels are all still the same, and you'll play through the variety rather quickly. The most interesting levels are only slightly better, but they put you at a crippling disadvantage.Most users will have trouble getting beyond the first few levels. The chances of a new player simply failing are high. Even as you progress, your odds don't get much better. A lot of the game boils down to focusing on the most effective strategies, there's no room for ""trial and error"".The game relies a little too much on dice rolls to create difficulty. Even if you have a sound strategy, you can easily be foiled by some random numbers. Most everything you do boils down to dice being rolled... Many actions involve multiple dice rolls to succeed.Basically, the game relies on dice rolls and enhancements to the opposing team to create a sense of difficulty. Unfortunately, this ends up being frustrating and tedious."
