76561197976777186,Recommended,276810,24730563,"Posted: 5 August, 2016",all,Dressel,"An X-Com esque soldier manager with a bit more depth to the character skills/stats.  Mordheim is a pretty damned unrelenting game.  Expect to lose the first few warbands you create while you're getting familiarized with the interface/UI and the different soldiers you can hire and what their strengths and weaknesses are.  The actual combat has a tendency to be nerve racking as you need to concentrate on both attacking whoever happens to be your enemy that round and collecting wyrdstone or loot from the battlefield so that you can continue to fund your warband.  And in order to collect anything off the battlefield your soldiers need to be standing at the end of the match, as any loot on KO'd units isn't collected.  This mechanic adds a lot of the stress and tension to the combat, as you'll find yourself cussing at the screen trying to find a possible way to save your one footsoldier with a full inventory mid match.  If you're a fan of the Warhammer franchise or turn based strategy games I think its worth checking out.  Just dont expect to master it within an hour."
