76561198095014795,Recommended,276810,24472648,"Posted: 22 July, 2016",all,entireleaves,I definitely recommend playing through ALL the tutorials and even then it might still be a bit confusing and take you a while to get into the game. It takes a bit to get the hang of things and can be VERY frustrating to new players but once you know what is going on the game is super fun and maybe even a little too easy.Some tips for new players:Arm all your henchmen with a 2-hand or dual wield maces. They only get one attack/turn to start and it needs to hit hard.Protect your leader! Henchmen are fairly expendable. Your leader is not and if he is wounded it will be a bit of a setback for a new player.Stick together! Keep all your members close together so they can protect each other and help each other out. If you send someone off alone to collect a distant bit of warpstone or loot they can easily get surrounded and killed before they get a chance to react.If you think you are going to lose a match try to loot some warpstone and put it in your cart. Whatever makes it into your cart is yours to keep at the end of the match even if you lose. This will help you keep up with deadlines for delivering warpstone.Remember early on if your leader or henchmen get wounds that will take days to recover from you can use reserve slots for them to recooperate in and hire new guys to go out on another run in the meantime.And finally if things go really badly you can always start a new warband and learn from your mistakes.I found it really maddening at first but once you figure out how it all works this is a really fun little game.
